esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Venture into Mazzatun, the \"Puzzle City\" of the Xit-Xaht tribe of Argonians, who have been forcing other Lizardfolk to work as slave labor on a project that has driven their masters … mad! Can you free them in time?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Centuries ago, the Empire made an ill-fated foray into the ruins an ancient Ayleid city. Follow in their footsteps with the treasure hunter, Tharayya, to discover what they sought and why they disappeared in the Depths of Malatar.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A group of Nordic graverobbers slaughtered their way into a long-hidden burial ground, intent on stealing ancient remains. Help the sentinel, Shelaria, on her quest for revenge and oust these nefarious plunderers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/icon_u29-dlc.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Under the ruins of the once-opulent Black Drake Villa, a grand library holds treasures and ancient tomes from across Tamriel. Gather your companions for a race against time to recover a mysterious book before dark forces burn everything to ash.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/icon_u29-dlc.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A fervent new cult has kidnapped innocent Dark Elves, dragging them to a lair deep within a long-abandoned mine. Join two unusual saviors to penetrate the defenses of the Cauldron and stop the Order of the Waking Flame from completing their deadly ritual.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/icon_u35-dlc.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/icon_u35-dlc.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Blind Path invades Bedlam Veil, Fa-Nuit-Hen calls on brave warriors to repel the invasion and discover what the cultists so desperately seek.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Naj-Caldeesh',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Talen-Lah and his band of necromancers run amok in the legendary lost xanmeer of Naj-Caldeesh. Stop them before their dark magic corrupts and destroys the ancient site.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Daedric forces have taken the Imperial City, and all three alliances vie to take it back. Experience hours of all-new PvP and PvE gameplay, both above ground and below, plus two new dungeons, never-before-seen monsters, craftable item sets, and more!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Join the Thieves Guild in Hew`s Bane, a never-before-seen area of Hammerfell! Explore Abah`s Landing, a decadent port town ruled by corrupt merchant lords, who struggle with the Thieves Guild for power. New stories, delves, world bosses, and much more!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Reports of mysterious shadow assassins draw you into Sotha Sil`s Clockwork City to investigate a new Daedric threat. Uncover the secrets of this strange new zone, take on a new 12-player trial, earn powerful new armor sets and items, and more.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'By royal decree, the once-forbidden island of the High Elves has been opened, its Crystal Tower drawing travelers to its light. But dark forces from beyond and below are also interested in the mystic location in the Summerset Isle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The word goes forth! Abnur Tharn, battlemage and former Imperial advisor, requires able-bodied allies to defend the cat-folk of Elsweyr against a rage of Dragons. Only the most brave need apply. Find Tharn in Riverhold, in Northern Elsweyr.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'To the heroes of Tamriel! Jorunn the Skald-King has dispatched agents to Western Skyrim to investigate and deal with a threat not only to Skyrim, but to all of Tamriel. Find the Skald-King`s agent in Solitude, the capital city of Haafingar Hold.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/icon_u28-dlc.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Society of the Steadfast calls all able-bodied adventurers to the island of High Isle in the Systres Archipelago to assist in a matter of great import to all alliances. Seek out Lady Arabelle Davaux in the city of Gonfalon Bay for details.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sorcerer-King Orgnum',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A Tales of Tribute deck telling the story of Orgnum, the Sorcerer-King.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A set of well-made thieves tools set within a leather pouch. One tool is missing, likely snatched by your thieving companion for her own amusement. \n\nPermanently grants the passive \"Ember`s Intuition\" to the bearer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Well-used clay vessels comprising a tea set. The kettle and a set of cups is etched with tentacles and eldritch runes. The whistle of the pot sounds like darkly whispered secrets.\n\nPermanently grants the passive \"Azandar`s Inquisitiveness\" to the bearer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A delicate clockwork gadget fashioned from second-hand materials and made to look like a hummingbird. Its long, thin copper tongue makes short work of even the toughest locks.\n\nPermanently grants the passive \"Tanlorin`s Finesse\" to the bearer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A walnut-sized bell ornately carved from jade. Detailed with electrum bezels and embossing, it once heralded the presence of a mischievous and much-loved cat named Ja`kh.\n\nPermanently grants the passive \"Zerith`s Guidance\" to the bearer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hard-earned knowledge, along with a bit of motivation of the tentacular kind, grants you faster movement throughout the Infinite Archive.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Every member of the Vosh Rakh religious movement hides his or her identity behind a golden mask of Orcish visage patterned after Trinimac`s own auric-tinged skin.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Plumed Wide-Brim Acorn-Warder',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Ever been to Valenwood and seen them huge graht-oaks? The biggest ones have acorns as big as your head. Yes! That big! Heavy, too, with points on `em. I won`t go into those woods without my Wide-Brim Acorn-Warder hat. Save your life.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Z`en Vengeance Kiss-Me-Not Cap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When a Wood Elf vows a Vengeance Oath to the god Z`en, they may wear this tusk-encrusted cap as a symbol of having sworn off physical affection until the vendetta is complete. Admittedly, the Kiss-Me-Not is also sometimes worn just as a joke.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Do you see yourself as a jaunty forest outlaw, plundering the rich and then making fools of the Town Guard as you escape into the nearby woods? Swashbuckle away with a quip, a song, and this devil-may-care Feathered Bycoket Cap!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The brash and extravagant Bull Antelope Tricorne is a favorite among Minotaur fanciers, Nord berserkers, and the Undaunted, who have little use for subtlety. It`s a hat that says, \"Back off, buddy.\" (Or perhaps, \"Let`s play ring-toss!\")',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Feel dapper yet cool under the desert sun by donning the Abah`s Watch Turban, the head-wrapping of the stylish Hew`s Bane guards!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'At your next desert soiree, be stylish yet mysterious, intriguing and tantalizing, by combining the Abah`s Watch Turban with a feature-concealing mask.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hedge Wizards, those itinerant folk-mages who cast minor spells for farmers and peasants, garner respect by wearing gear that`s just a bit outrageous and intimidating—like the Claw Cap favored by the Hoodoo Tinkers of the Dragontail Mountains.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In the traveling comedy troupes of Tamriel, the recurring mage character is known as Fantasticus the Clever Man, and he wears the signature broad-brimmed pointy hat that just says \"wizard\" to the average citizen.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dwarf-Style Mage`s Hat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This Dwarven-themed conical wizard hat and goggles is offered this season by Jork, the famous Tailor-Thane of Windhelm. \"If the Dwarves were still around, and if Dwarves had wizards, I bet this is just what they`d wear!\" says the irrepressible Jork.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This fanciful take on the cap and goggles of the legendary Imperial Mananauts, adapted by Diocletia of Skingrad from an old engraving, is this season`s must-have item for fashionable wizards of the Mages Guild.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s a Witches Festival tradition to masquerade as Hollowjack the Pumpkin Spectre, menacing the adults and mock-frightening the timid. If that sounds like fun to you, this mask is just what you`re looking for.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Wise-Wing the Owl is associated in northern Tamriel with the god Jhunal or Julianos. During the Witches Festival she is said to warn the unwary away from graveyards and witches` covens where they may come to harm.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A Colovian fur hood, double-stitched and plain.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bi-Color Coxcomb Cap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even fools and jesters have a hierarchy—only the best-looking or most aristocratic are entitled to call themselves Coxcombs and wear the coveted Bi-Color Cap! Do you think you qualify?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ass-Ears Jester Cap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Back in the First Era, fools and harlequins used to wear actual donkey ears on their hats as symbols of their profession. Over time the floppy ears have become merely symbolic, but the Ass-Ears Jester Cap is still charmingly goofy.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Just because your headwear serves as woodland camouflage, that doesn`t mean it can`t be comfy-warm!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '12-Point Antler Skullcap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The rank of a Hunter of Hircine is said to be marked by the number of points on his cap`s antlers. Plus they`re always prepared for a game of ring-toss!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '14-Point Antler Skullcap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Awarded only to the most mischievous and mirthful pranksters, this jingling gold-like crown is a symbol of great status during the Jester`s Festival.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This is a re-creation of the Crested Hood worn by the light infantry of Dumac`s Own Royal Skirmishers at the Battle of Red Mountain.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Dwarven tonal architects were careful to wear deflective headgear to protect their ears and thought-organs against harmonic feedback fluctuations. \"The Tonal Attenuator is clear evidence that the Dwemer lacked all concept of glamor\" —Guylaine Marilie',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once a person reaches a certain station in life, they wish to dress so as to reflect that honor and dignity, if only out of self-respect. The Sadrith Mora Quilted Snood sends the message that you are a person of consequence in the community.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though the spikes on this so-called \"miter\" look aggressive, scholars of the long-lost Dwemer believe they actually functioned as \"etheric antenna,\" helping to pull in long-distance \"Thought Calls.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This is a replica of the headgear scholars of the Dwarves believe was worn by the \"Tuathumz\" or \"central pylon\" of their Thought Calling system. The three finials are either broadcast-foci, or convenient tabs for wall hanging.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s a Witches Festival tradition to masquerade as Hollowjack the Hollowjack Spectre, menacing the adults and mock-frightening the timid. If that sounds like fun to you, this mask is just what you`re looking for.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bull-Heart Skull Sallet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This barbaric helm partly made from the skull of a bull is much like those worn by the Bull-Heart Warriors of the Reach in their savage Horned Triumph ritual.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stag-Heart Skull Sallet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This antlered helm is like those worn by the Stag-Heart Reachmen, a sect that worships the Daedric Prince Hircine in his aspect of Uricanbeg, the Great Stag whose hooves drum the Blood Summons.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Crow-Heart Skull Sallet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some Reachclans are ruled by Hagravens, and those feathered terrors are protected by a personal guard known as Crow-Heart Warriors. Their fearsome helmets appear to incorporate the skull of a great predatory bird.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Keptu-Horn Skull Sallet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Be prepared for white-out conditions in the blizzards of northern Skyrim—or just radiate squinty-eyed danger in this face-concealing protective hood.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Blights, flus, and plagues may bedevil Tamriel, but even the most dedicated Plague Doctor needs a little casual down-time now and then in order to keep those epidemics in check. Put down that mortar and pestle and head down to the tavern for some ale!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Not satisfied with a mere garland of fir on your chapeau? Go all-out with the Winter Wreath Broadbrim, which wraps the entire top of your hat in festive New Life greens, holly, berries, and cones. It`s a party on your head!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Clockwork Apostles who must venture into the frequently-inclement weather outside the Brass Fortress protect their eyes and faces by wearing a Radius Mask of synthetic wool and vitrine. Mysterious!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Apostles who still have their original, organic lungs may want to protect them out in the Radius by investing in a full-hood Rebreather, which keeps out the storm-blown metallic motes that can lead to \"brass lung.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This full-coverage articulated metal mask is like a Brass Fortress for your head, providing maximum protection against both environmental contaminants and walking into low-hanging pipes.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This full-face visor looks as if an Atronach`s flaring features had been captured in metal, giving its wearer the otherworldly look of an elemental Daedra from Oblivion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You know what`s great? If you add a standing collar to a hood and half-mask, it suddenly makes you look more dangerous, sinister, and threatening. That`s what.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blackmarrow Necro-Turban',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Raise the dead in style in your Blackmarrow Necro-Turban, featuring a sinister upper-face half-visor and twin metallo-antlers. Pairs well with zombie mounts and the Fang Lair crafting style.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_flatbrim-mourning_01.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_flatbrim-mourning_02.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_flatbrim-mourning_03.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_helsing-vampire_03.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_helsing-vampire_01.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hat_helsing-vampire_02.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dread-Etched Dragon Priest Mask',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Used to be that hacking up crypt-dust was just part of the trade. But times have changed, eh? Take a look at this hood and mask. Won`t keep the stink of a rotting skeever out of your nose, but it`ll help you breathe a little easier.\"—Paurges Aline',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"For our skills to flourish, we lend our magic to ice and spite. Each frost-tainted conjuration and ritual we conduct grants us strength and germinates the wicked seed of power within us.\"—Gohlla',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Stand out from the crowd with this dramatic tam! Crafted from the finest fabrics in High Rock and blessed by priests of Dibella, this hat promises to give you a pop of eye-catching splendor any bard would envy.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Reach-Mage Ceremonial Skullcap',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This mask only hints at your blood-drenched desires. Revel in your passions and feed with no restraint.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Breezes tease your feathered crest when you venture forth wearing this helm. Styled after the piece worn by Keshu the Black Fin, this Argonian-crafted headwear exhibits your dedication to this leader`s optimistic vision for her people.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally created by a now-forgotten Breton whose search for knowledge of obscure magic led him into the Deadlands, this innovative headgear is a must-have for any wandering the unforgiving wilds of Oblivion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Blend into the crowds of Tamriel`s cities and beyond while protecting your head from the environment with this soft-to-the-touch hood. It feels so good you might never want to take it off!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Whether you`re attending masquerades in High Isle or Daggerfall, this mask and hood provides you with stylish anonymity. Keep one in your pack for those last-minute invitations to another royal gala.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"If you see a soldier with a swooping carrion bird on their helm, walk away. They`re Imperials, sure, but this band of warriors survives the Cyrodiil warzone using tactics that would make a Dremora blush.\"—Hingor Netch-Eater',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sailor-at-Arms Helm',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When confronting foes on a ship`s deck, you need head protection that fits snugly and provides cushion against potential blows. Luckily, armorer Arienne Mathierry of Gonfalon Bay crafted just the thing for warrior-sailors like you!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The flame of knowledge burns brightly within you, eclipsed only by this obsidian-tempered mask wrought by the Firesong Circle. Though they protect the rites used to shape their magma-born armor, they gift these masks to those who share their love of lore.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After Umaril the Unfeathered bound himself to Meridia`s realm, he started his \"ruin-from-afar\" campaigns, sending servants out to deal with his foes. The commanders among them wore these helms to denote their rank within each group.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"You`re not one of us until you hunt down and skin a skeever for your cap. If you pick up a disease along the way, so much the better.\"—Peryite`s Chosen Two-Toes Cadra',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dominion War-Locks',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Going to war may mean donning a helm, but beneath it an honored Dominion warrior is entitled to wear these official Alliance War-Locks, which keep long hair under control while still looking superb.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dominion Lizard-Locks',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Going to war may mean donning a helm, but beneath it an Argonian Dominion warrior is entitled to wear these official Alliance Lizard-Locks, which keep beaded bristles under control while still looking superb.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even more legendary than the unicorn is that imaginary two-horned beast called the rhinoceros. Live the legend with Lizard Rhinoceros horns!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Short-Spiked Crest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Inspired by the mesas and buttes of southern Hammerfell, this updo is a striking look for your next semi-formal affair.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This feline warriors` favorite consists of a handsome long mane, gathered in three places by turquoise-studded pewter clasps. Fierce but not entirely informal.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Shaved to port, with a radical comb-over to starboard. You look like you mean business, soldier.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This topknot crest descending into a triple-wrapped braided ponytail is both warlike and practical, and is often worn by those soldiers who worship Alkosh, the Dragon-Cat.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Six-Spike Parietal Array',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Fore-and-Aft Webbed Spike Crest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left-Parted Bob',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Tight-Curled Hair Helmet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Right-Parted Cropped',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left-Parted Cropped',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Long Pulled-Back Pony',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Widow`s Peak Comb-Back',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mini-Pony with Braids',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Short Back-Pulled Pony',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Center-Part Medium',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Center-Part Long',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Why bother with spines or spikes when your skull can sprout a fountain of feathers? You`ll be the fanciest lizard in the mud-wallow.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Covenant War-Locks',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Going to war may mean donning a helm, but beneath it an honored Covenant warrior is entitled to wear these official Alliance War-Locks, which keep long hair under control while still looking superb.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Covenant Lizard-Plumes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Going to war may mean donning a helm, but beneath it an Argonian Covenant warrior is entitled to wear these official Alliance Lizard-Plumes, which keep out of a helmet`s way while still looking superb.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Rotmeth Hangover Bed-Head',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mane-of-Many-Rivers',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Feathered Kelp-Scalp',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Seaweed head-feathers were first popularized by the aquatic hunter Lurks-in-Murk of Helstrom.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mid-Parted Shoulder-Length',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As an archer, I like to have a windvane right on my noggin,\" says Tlaxal-Hei of Thorn.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Multi-Spined Skull Crest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This menacing look is a favorite of surly teen-aged Argonians in the more unsavory parts of Gideon.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Assassin-Style Sunset Crest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This season the hairstyles of the Morag Tong are all the rage—even among the usually Dark Elf-averse Argonians!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Bangs with ear-length sides is the hallmark hairstyle of Royal Pages across Tamriel. This variant is a little wilder, for a page with rage.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Nord sea raiders from the coasts of Skyrim first popularized this style, a visible demonstration of its wearer`s commitment to going all-in. Not for the cautious.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The wind-swept waves of the Sea of Ghosts is no place for bare heads, fanciful hats, or a loose shaggy mane. Keep your locks bound as tightly as your sails with these ropy braids and horker-tusk charms and you`ll have no fear of the harshest gales.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Your tongue isn`t the only sharp thing about you—your keen coif can slice right through the pompous bluster of even the stodgiest get-together.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'About to leap into battle? Or pirouette into a gala? Do so knowing that you are both well-coiffed and richly accessorized.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/hair_u_hu_coiled-bob.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Derik Hallin of the mid-First Era popularized tightly coiled short hair, specifically among sword-singers. Since then, some among us who study the Book of Circles created variants for Khajiit and Argonians who wish to learn our ways.\"—Khazha of Sentinel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Keen-Edged Shag',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those who work in the shadows need hairstyles as sharp as their blades. With this no-fuss shag cut, you`re quickly set for your latest assignation … or assassination.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/marking_face_unisex_humanoid_the-aurbic-eye.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Side Half-Coal Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Right Side Half-Coal Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'V-Y-Y Black Paint Strokes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Large Black-and-Blue Domino',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Burn-Scarred Nose and Chin',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Double-Scarred Left Eye',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Right Cheek-Chin Diagonal Scar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Cheek-Chin Diagonal Scar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Claw-Scarred Brow and Nose',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Red Over-Nose Blood Bridle',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Nose-Radiant Blood Smears',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Side Half-Green Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Side Half-Red Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Side Half-Brown Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Right Side Half-Blue Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'V-Y-Y Brown Paint Strokes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Left Side Half-Chalk Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The sprig-and-leaves face tattoo known as the Wild Vines denotes a follower of the nature deity called Y`ffre or Jephre.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Warrior-Poet Face Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Decorate your epidermis with writhing, sinuous, barbed fingers of mystic energy evoking the imagery associated with Lord Vivec, Tribune and Warrior-Poet of Morrowind!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some say the Mundus is naught but a great Mechanism, and we are but animunculi, like Dwarven automatons, turning like gears in some universal clockwork. But some mortals are just motorheads, you know? These machine-inspired face markings are for them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This design symbolizing the intertwining of all life forms is popular with wyresses, Wardens, Y`ffre-worshipers, and all those who feel a special connection with Nature in Tamriel.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Eye-Briar Gemmed Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This begemmed Eye-Briar face tattoo gives one a barbaric beauty that`s both wild and sophisticated, at home in the big city or around a wilderness campfire.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Eagle: symbol of the Aldmeri Dominion and totem of the High Elves, expressing their soaring ambition to be pre-eminent in whatever they choose to pursue. This tasteful Face Tattoo displays one`s allegiance to that ideal.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This Skull Face Tattoo with a hard-edged Spoked design is worn by those who wish to honor the dead through a day of special remembrance—or just want to look coolly intimidating.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those who`ve run afoul of the Followers of the Manbeast, Lord Hircine, may bear the crimson scars of their encounter for the rest of their lives. Badge of honor? Symbol of devotion? Trophy of a battle well-fought? That`s for you to judge.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Chalk Face Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful face daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in sharp white chalk dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Woad Face Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful face daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful blue woad dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Algae Face Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful face daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful green algae dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Yolk Face Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful face daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful hackwing egg-yolk dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Blood Face Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the fierce Dead-Water tribe goes to a formal declaration of conflict, the warriors daub themselves with red dye that resembles smears of blood.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"All will see your fierceness plainly as it is now writ upon your face in Dragonsmoke.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Warrior-Poet Skull Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Colorful and intimidating. Truly, these markings bring the fire of the warrior-poet to your spirit as well as to your face.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Dancing among the Dragons. Wounding. Killing. It`s not a job for the faint of heart. Whatever your motivation, and whatever your hunting methods, this facial mark expresses your resolve to destroy those creatures known as Dragons.\" —Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Many Dragons have fallen before your might. Many respect your prowess in combat. And with these green-glowing markings, even those unfamiliar with Dragon hunting will suspect your ferocity.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Each of us has deep darkness within us. And we choose what to do with that darkness. You? You need reminding of that. Winged darkness, yes, to give you strength as you fly through shadowed times.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Within you is the spirit of the First Cat`s Pride. Let us bring that golden fire to the surface so that others may gaze upon your spirit directly, then react with awe.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"People act like what we do is amoral, but you retrieve a trinket from their long-dead grandpa, and they`re all smiles. Just don`t forget to mark yourself as one of us before you start work, or we might mistake you for draugr!\"—Paurges Aline',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Upon their one-year anniversary of service guarding the border of the Reach, members of the Karthwatch garrison have an informal tradition of getting a knotwork band tattooed across their foreheads to signify that they held the line.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Paint Dibella`s beauty in gentle strokes upon your cheek so that all will know your muse and feel her touch when you caress the hearts of your audience.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The road to Sovngarde requires bravery. Courage. Perseverance. And much death, including yours. Wear the symbol of this path upon your face—to warn others that you stand your ground in even the most desperate plights.\"—Gerda Swift-Sword',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Windracers, sworn to protect Whiterun, learn their way around town without relying on vision. After they survive their first night battle, they gain facial markings to note their skill and courage.\"—Gerda Swift-Sword',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Favored among the Markarth Sisters, these blood-red markings signify one who fiercely defends the natural world while walking among the wilds and cities alike.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'They say you`re bolder than a starving skeever, deadlier than a rutting troll, and quieter than the fallen dead—you had to be to earn this tattoo from the artist-thieves in the Riften Ratway.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blessed Life-Tree Face Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mrf_aylied-.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The mysteries surrounding the ancient ruins of Ayleid civilization are many. How you returned from your last Ayleid endeavor with the markings of the blessed life-tree on your face remains one of them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sul-Xan Prophet Face Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Sul-Xan designed their markings to emulate the elaborate stonework of the xanmeer pyramids. Painting lines on their cheeks and chins before battle ensures that they will remain steadfast and resolute, no matter the danger or the cost.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sul-Xan Raider Face Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sul-Xan tattooists often fall into a bloody reverie when applying face paint to their warrior kin. Acidic dyes make their frenzied artistry dangerous for the eyes, but those who lose their sight in throes of chaos are doubly blessed!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those who wrap themselves in Mephala`s web and help spin her secretive plots sometimes develop the keen night-eyes of her spiderkith. Ideal for navigating the complex strands of the Spiral Skein, but easily blinded by the light.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Inspired by their devotion to Xivilai warriors, Gleamwoe cultists in Shadowfen trickle pigment carefully down their cheek and add more dripping lines with every high-ranking noble they kill.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As the first roses of the season bloom, Sanguine`s followers gather in candlelit gardens to caress each other`s faces with ink—tracing a rose-shaped path of pain and pleasure along both brows and cheeks.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Crimson Trickster hides his face with painted smiles and eerie grace. Two-thirds red and one-third white, this comic face is quite a sight! If mischief is what brings you glee, this paint will suit your revelry!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Only the fiercest and most skilled warrior-smiths of the Ket Keptu earned the right to bear these two-toned face tattoos. Do you craft your own weapons and wield them in battle? If so, wear these marks proudly.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Any who seek to find loopholes in the Stricture of Fargrave know better than to do so when they see these Grasp-favored facial designs nearby. You may not be of the Grasp, but giving shady Daedra pause while in the Bazaar? Worth the marks!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Though many dispute whether Khenarthi, S`rendarr, or another spirit grants these jade-green eyes to blessed individuals, all agree on one thing: Those who discover and share the location of an oasis to those in need earn them.\"—Sulema, Initiate Scholar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Battle-Scarred Visage',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Want to earn respect from High Isle sailors? Laugh in the face of a mast-shearing storm between here and Amenos, plus feed a few pirates to the fishes, and I`ll ink your face so that all know your spirit.\"—Florent Renaudin, Tattoo Artist',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Instead of looking to recreate the mountains or symmetry of stones, Stonelore Druids developed a pattern of looping swirls and harsh line breaks. They paint it in charcoal and ash around one eye to represent the ever-watchful gaze of Y`ffre.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Strokes of golden joy embracing rings of azure and bronze. These call attention to the spark of enduring happiness within you. You already love the idea of it, I can tell. Make it a reality.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The twists and turns of a magister`s mind become more pronounced the longer they bend their will to spore crafting. Perhaps it`s the organic ebb and flow of the fungus? Flora flows into fascinating function. But you know that, yes?\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Feather and claw. Marked for a Briarheart, eh? What called you? Reachfolk dreams? Daedric nightmares? A persuasive witch? All of these and more? It matters not to me. I simply want a chance to examine your facial ink.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Vaermina cult leader Larul first wore this facial design while presiding over a lich-making ritual. Her gleeful laughter still echoes in the damp caverns of Kingscrest Cavern. Yet, in the waking world, she is nowhere to be found.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Librarians possess mixed feelings about any who exhibit the eye-framing swirls of Hermaeus Mora. These curators of knowledge honor erudition among those who seek their tomes, yet they fear the covetousness that can drive agents of the Golden Eye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"What you call reality is drudgery. We truly live only during the hours of sleep, when the Weaver of Dreams welcomes us into her many-layered nest of truth. See my face? This art marks that I`m hers. Live your true life. Join us.\"—Dreamdelver Marbruk',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"After a time, I found myself in the wending, ever-coiling hallways of a labyrinth. Despite the crepuscular atmosphere, I saw carved meter and verse `pon the walls. The words crept behind my eyes. Beneath my skin. As you can see.\" —Scribe Maylen',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Face Art',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Skaal artists scribe waved bands, signs of the All-Maker`s grace, upon the brows of the worthy. The ink they use combines the All-Maker`s six gifts: earth, fauna, flora, sun, water, and wind.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The confrontation between the Star-Made Knight and Umaril the Unfeathered will fade into memory unless we keep it alive. Pelinal freed many from oppression. I hope, by inking my face, to invite conversations about this topic.\"—Lucius the Earnest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Inspired by the Mages Guild, these markings use ingredients mixed into ink by an alchemical master. An illusion-working around the eyes finishes this mystical effect.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Please the filers of the Infinite Archive, and they may just grant you a facial tattoo to commemorate your time beyond the stacks. Who could pass up an ink-themed tattoo that uses archival ink and makes your eye color pop?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"My mother wasn`t pleased when she saw what I had inked on my scales. She would`ve preferred a rendition of the Hist or something from the Black Marsh. But I just like roses more.\"—Paints-with-Mud, Murkmire',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Stylized raven art exists in several Tamrielic cultures. Artist-Adept Aimira, who created this tattoo, wanted something minimalist to draw attention to the eyes. \"I pulled on the themes I used in the body art. The overall effect is fierce, is it not?\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Face Soul-Mark of the Sapiarchs',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stone-Nest Orator Face Paint',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"There is no light without darkness. No fullness without hunger. No life without death. Such are the teachings of the great Dragons.\"—Fire and Ash, by Fjot Tale-keeper',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'World-Eater Eyes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The World-Eater, the Twilight God, the First Dragon—no matter the name, Alduin casts a long shadow over Nirn. However, many dedicated followers of his cult find wisdom in the darkness, and a certain freedom in his hunger.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Varmiina gifts her servants with the Sight of Dark Portents. Some claim they see the future with their glowing eyes. But consider that she may just show you what she wants you to see, yes?\"—Mazza-Mirri`s Guide to Dark Spirits',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Nightmare tendrils caress your skin. They taste the coppery blood-tears flowing from your eyes. And they mark you as one who belongs forever to Vaermina.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Warriors from Orsinium make excellent models, yes? So strong and stoic. But throw color on them and they strut like any freshly groomed Senche-raht. Fazudah just wishes they were shorter. Hard to paint their faces up there.\"—Fazudah',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'By fury of outward expression be forewarned. Choose not to heed that warning, and icy wrath from void-dark eyes may be the last thing you see.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Move with the current. Find the waters of the ibis and dance, warrior. Then come back to face me and earn markings like mine.\"—Farja Ibis-Dancer',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Stand tall if you wish to emulate ancient sailors of the Warrior Wave. But be ready to flow like the seas themselves. When you master their ways, I have a marking for you.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stone-Nest Xanmeer Face Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some Stone-Nest builders who explore their guardianship of stone choose to tattoo their faces with sacred mineral pigments. The people of Xor-Hist now share this practice with those who understand that what they craft will live well beyond their years.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Four-Spike Wattle',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Four-Spike Wattle is an arrangement of throat spines particularly popular on the coastal shores of Thornmarsh.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The double-waxed \"Squid Goatee\" is a favorite of the dapper sailors of Tamriel`s southern coasts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hey, kitten, what`s sexier than that just-got-out-of-bed look … on tufts of hair in front of your ears? Nothing, that`s what. (If you`re a Khajiit.)',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Two-Spike Goatee',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'V-Spiked Unibrow',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'White-Gold Eyeshadow',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This mystic eye-shading is a favorite of members of the Mages Guild, as it makes their eyes resemble the guild`s famous magic-eye symbol. Enchanting!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Proudly masculine facial hair, the Brigand`s Beard projects authority, power, and a devil-may-care attitude.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Howling winds and piercing cold may give some heroes pause, but not you! Show off your icy determination with your frost-covered face.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Old Salt`s Chin-Trinket',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The so-called \"Talon Veil\" is worn by Cat-Folk who have passed the dangerous initiation rites of a Khajiiti hunting club.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Azure Brow-to-Temple Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Elven Infinity Half-Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Metalwing Half-Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Tiara Half-Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Scholar`s Half-Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ice-Blue Begonia',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Julianos` avian companion, Wise-Wing, is usually represented as a barred owl, so wearing barred owl tail-feathers often bespeaks devotion to the God of Wisdom.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Shaman`s Bird-Bone Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sometimes you just feel barbaric, and then only wearing a naked bird-skull on your forehead will do.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Yes, I like to wear a skull on my skull. More skulls are always better than fewer, are they not?\" —Adzi-Loh',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Eight-Fang Nose Chain',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You`ll swing your tail to the Two Moons Dance with pride when it`s tipped with the so-sleek Sporty Tail Tuft. Clan Mother approved!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Six-Spike Tail Trim',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'They`ll give you plenty of room to yourself in the mud wallow when you show up wearing your dangerous-looking Six-Spike Tail Trim. Erect the spine of passive aggression!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dwarf-Style Sun Goggles',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When your entire civilization lives in subterranean cities, you devise high-quality goggles to protect your eyes from the blinding sun of the surface world! Dress to impress with these stylish bronze shades inspired by the long-lost Dwarves of the deeps.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dwarf-Style Brow Shields',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These high-concept Dwarven adornments are like pauldrons—for your face! If anyone asks you what they`re for, just waggle your brows, smile, and say, \"Bthun nchuan.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Deep Elf Goggle-Horn',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Scholars of the vanished Dwarven race theorize that this device augmented Dwemeri vision by adding an elevated \"third eye\" that added time-perspective to depth perception. We just like the way it looks!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This omnigatherum based on designs discovered in the Dwarven ruin of Nchuleft combines the Brow Shields and the Goggle Horn into one mighty upper-face visor that`ll have you saying, \"Thuabtharng btham!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Made Circlet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"And upon the Star-Made Circlet there shall be Three Diamonds in remembrance of our Glorious Empire`s Foundation: One Diamond for Alessia, One Diamond for Morihaus, and One Diamond for Pelinal, also called Whitestrake.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Made Sword Coronet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As a Star-Made Knight, this victor`s laurel wreath will sit lightly on your brow, informing everyone you meet of your legendary triumph. Hail and kudos!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Made Diamond Diadem',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"But Al-Esh thought it meet to retain the Laureled Diadem for her own Imperial Brow, and it was set with Twin Red Diamonds, one for Herself and one for Belharza to Come, who was even then Quickening.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Naryu Virian says, \"When you take out a target, these Morag Tong-style goggles will keep spattering blood out of your eyes, so you can see your way clear to make your escape when the local guards come after you!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This is a replica of the impressive tiara awarded to Clockwork Apostles when they reach the rank of Mechanist. Congratulations, Gear-Champion!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Brow Diadem',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This metallic tiara, with its central, stylized Dragon head, its mouth ever-gaping in Eternal Hunger, was popular in the lower-level clergy of the Dragon Cult, according to scholars of those ancient times.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This metal-studded Leather Brow Band is as practical as it is decorative. After all, a barbarian warrior might have a little too much mead, miss the doorway a bit, and BANG. Best to have a bit of protection for the old noggin, am I right?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wire Cage Half-Mask',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'For the strong and untamed spirit, the spiraling wires of this jewelry half-mask express the inner power that no cage could ever contain.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/adornment_both_all_wolfsbane-flower.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Tooth-and-Tusk Tiara',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Dead-Water Tribe of Naga Argonians are a spiky lot to begin with, and when they want to look tough, they just pile on more spikes. This trick works for just about anyone, really.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Our best artisans crafted this jeweled laurel based on my research of past Proving Festivals. It is our hope that by wearing these laurels, we can become closer to our honored ancestors.\"—Magnate Feina-Darak',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Prize-Hunter`s Patch',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Dragons call the lands of Skyrim `Keizaal,` and thus we shall name this coronet, which only the worthiest of a Dragon warrior-priest`s servants may don.\"—Azhidal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Before the Interregnum, this elegant circlet graced the brows of High Elves who attended the Shimmerene Soiree, a gala held by the Canonreeve to honor that city-state. Now artisans sell it to any who wish to be appropriately garbed for this festivity.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A self-described Saliache artist-warrior described how she wore this stunning tiara to shapeshifting exhibitions to assist in transformations. While I can`t garner the same results, it catches the light and draws eyes at gatherings.\"—Savre Longleat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The lone surviving member of a now-forgotten Reach clan woke up after a night spent at a shrine to Mehrunes Dagon with this thorny crown upon her brow and a grim purpose. Those who follow her earn a similar adornment after trials best not spoken aloud.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stallion-Liege Brow Medallion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After Sai Sahan freed Leyawiin from its Longhouse occupation, Leyawiin honored those who aided him with a special medallion. Each year since, the city awards these Nibenese-style head ornaments to its bravest defenders.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As you feel the crown`s weight, let the clang of steel, the scent of ash, and the taste of blood fill your mind. Now stand, Razor-pledged. Let your ambition guide you along Dagon`s path.\"—Disastrix Zansora',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Draw attention away from your hands—and perhaps your mischief—with this impressive ornament. Though once worn only by Dremora as a sign of status, these flashy diadems now grace the heads of cunning thieves and bold Daedra-slayers alike.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once granted only to those who performed a service to the nobility of Summerset, this crest later saw wider use during the Alinor-Lillandril skirmishes of 2E 320. Those fighting for Alinor wore them to help them identify fellow skirmishers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chimer Half-Mask',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Each piece of this ornate head jewelry represents a trial that I passed to gain the title of Evoker. You may not see Eyevea-trained evokers like me wearing these every day. But for formal occasions? Just the thing.\"—Evoker Triann',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Keep your hair, fur, or feathers untangled and well-coiffed! All with a distinctive hairpin bearing the visage of Hermaeus Mora. While it may not utter dark secrets into your ear, its glint may attract someone who can share intriguing mysteries with you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"You never walk alone under the All-Maker`s gaze. The fur and leather in this band are a reminder that all are One. Meanwhile its gentle pressure on your head can keep you grounded to unbroken earth.\"—Skaal Shaman Rik',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some would argue that bearing the image of Molag Bal for something as trifling as a masquerade is borderline folly, but to the mask-loving revelers of Tamriel, the Prince`s iconic silhouette is simply too good to pass up.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Delvers of underground spaces often bring back smaller pieces of this material for use in crafting flower-laden tiaras. Merchants now proclaim their intentions to bring these baubles to the mainland as beautiful curiosities.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Orc-Style Snow Goggles',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This pearl-encrusted, beaded veil masks the features of those ritual belly dancers who perform in Hammerfell and Tamriel`s south.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Quarter-Moon Earrings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wing-Lobes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ear-Runes',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Three-Hoop Earrings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Two-Loop Earrings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sabre Cat Ear-Fang',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The sabre-teeth of northern Tamriel`s great hunting cats make truly imposing earrings!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dangling Triple-Chain Earrings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Jaw-Fin Fringe',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s said that a warrior of the Dead-Water tribe saw the impressive sideburns on a Breton general and decided it was a look that could be improved upon with Jaw-Fins. Wise decision.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Dancers among the Baandari Pedlars wear this tassel-laden veil that chimes and jingles with every move. Now it can be yours for a song … or a dance!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Moon-and-Star Earrings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Upon the felling of the maples, Y`ffre wept. Her amber tears glistened before dropping onto the leaves, encasing them in lamentation-given-form. Picking one up, she said, `Wear these in memory of this day.` And they did.\"—Grove-Death of the Maples',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Skaal tales suggest the symbols on these earrings were already on trees and rocks discovered when the first Nords came to Solstheim. The All-Maker moves in mysterious, and sometimes fashionable, ways.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Adventure-Ending Arrow',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Why make eye-catching earrings from Coldharbour`s very fabric? I need explain nothing to one such as you, worm casting. Die!\"—Cirterisse of Coldharbour',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A high-end chef`s outfit that indicates the wearer is a provisioner supreme.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This jovial jester garb, including mask and bell-cap, could even make a zombie smile.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ordinator Night-Raid Armor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When rounding up criminal scum or raiding hives of heresy in the dark of night, the Temple`s Ordinators don this night-dark armor.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Full plate armor with blue-black accents, topped by an armet helm with open visor, as worn by the Lion Guard of the Covenant.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Plate and scale mail armor of whitened steel with golden accents, with a heavy close-helm, as seen on the Lion Guard Elite.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Lightweight thieving outfit of dark-gray padded cloth and leather, with a feature-concealing half-balaclava.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Tree-Minder',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The classic dark-gold armor worn by Ordinators of the Tribunal while keeping the peace and combating heresy in Mournhold and its surrounding regions.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This Sheogorath-approved jester outfit displays the three faces of madness.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Show some class with this opulent yet restrained aristocrat`s ensemble for the high-toned and the haughty.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Soul-Shriven Ragged Clothing',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Soul-Shriven arrive in Coldharbour, they are garbed in cast-off rags taken from the dead.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Soul-Shriven Leather Outfit',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Soul-Shriven arrive in Coldharbour, some are garbed in cast-off leathers taken from the dead.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Soul-Shriven Armor Outfit',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Soul-Shriven arrive in Coldharbour, some are garbed in cast-off armor taken from the dead.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume replicates the full-helmed armor worn by the warriors of the ancient Perena tribe of Nedes.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Fighters Guild Warm-Weather Gear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume replicates the look of the Fighters Guild warm-weather uniform.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Fighters Guild Cool-Weather Gear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume replicates the look of the Fighters Guild cool-weather uniform.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Off-the-Shoulder Evening Dress',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'High-Collared Coin Ball Gown',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sand-Kissed Salwar Ensemble',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In Orsinium these days, even the busiest tusker likes some flair in his clothing—and nothing says \"modern Orc\" like a bias-cut-placket tunic from Borzighu at Coldsnap Clothiers. \"This outfit,\" he says, \"is one for the ages!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Jo-m`Athra Spellcaster Suit',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Possibly the most feared of the dro-m`Athra are their spellcasters, the jo-m`Athra, Khajiiti wizards who became \"bent\" into Lost Cats.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dar-m`Athra Stealth Outfit',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The dar-m`Athra are the stealthiest of the dro-m`Athra, and therefore rarely seen, except for a final glimpse as one kills you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Do-m`Athra Battle Armor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When warrior-dos are \"bent\" into dro-m`Athra, they become that fearsome variety the Khajiit call a do-m`Athra.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The clean traditional lines of this gown evoke the wakes of Torinaan`s ships when they first discovered Auridon,\" says designer Estinwe Silkdancer. \"Its classic majesty is a reminder that even the lowest-ranked Altmer is still a High Elf.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Estinwe the Muse of Shimmerene says, \"Evening in Alinor, and starlight glistens from swirling sashes and silver circlets as Elf maidens prance through the time-hallowed steps of the First Founders` Fast Pavane. Say hey!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Budi-Shirt and Galligaskins',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Samsu the Sleek says, \"This season in Mistral we`re tightening up the traditional billowing budi to give it a more streamlined silhouette, and shortening it the better to show off our breeze-catching galligaskin trousers. So comfy!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Moon-Sugar Festival Suit',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When the Moon-Sugar cane is ripe for harvest, and Jone and Jode are both waning crescents, it`s time for the sweetest festival of the year,\" says designer Samsu the Sleek. \"This Festival Suit blends five different silks so you`ll look shiny and sharp!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Rimmen Fountain-Side Loungewear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pellitine Tea-Fete Gown',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Graht-Climber`s Active Wear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Stitchmaster Moneriel says, \"We all have days when we have to climb the graht-oak to clean the house-pod gutters. Does that mean you have to dress like a frump? Of course not! Look trim and stylish in my latest halter-and-skirt outfit from Elden Root!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Doeskin-and-Chamois Woods Wear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Covering yourself from head to toe makes perfect sense,\" says Moneriel of Elden Root, \"if you`re a Breton! Ha!\" You`ll feel free and easy in any social situation in this light doeskin-and-chamois affair accented with turquoise and sea-beads.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some occasions call for formal wear,\" says Stitchmaster Moneriel of Elden Root. \"You may have to attend an important event, but you can still turn heads from trunk to treetop in my thousand-beaded ceremonial dress!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Inspired by the majestic and imposing attire of the Imperial Elder Council, this tunic and sash ensemble by Diocletia of Skingrad is suitable for high-profile occasions from the formal to the celebratory. Show off the proud heritage of the Empire!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When you specialize in venoms and poison-making, you invest in special protective garb to keep from being poisoned by your own experiments—or else! And if your clients are just a little intimidated by your creepy attire, all the better.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once, it is said, a cult of Dragon-worshipers ruled all of northern Tamriel. Their leaders were Dragon Priests, cruel clerics of great power who hid their faces under magical masks. Now you can wear the semblance of these legendary magi.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ever Damp Reed-Fiber Kilt',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Now you can avoid the vexation of dry-scale thigh-chafing with the new \"Ever Damp\" kilt-of-reeds, available from Jaxa the Hermit in every Argonian`s favorite color: mud-brown! (Though you may dye them else-wise, should such be your whim, egg-sibling.)',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Upriver Striped Sash-Kilt',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Be the best-dressed lizard in the xanmeer in this striped reed-fiber kilt with over-and-under shoulder sashes! Alternating panels of mud-brown and sandbar will say \"Do you wallow? So do I!\" to every Argonian you meet.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'For the Saxhleel who dares to scintillate, the reclusive Jaxa the Hermit presents this season`s must-have formal-wear, the multi-layered Marshlord robe set, sewn with the shiny shells of thousands of tiny swamp insects!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Designing for conditions in Vvardenfell is a stimulating challenge,\" says Voldsea Arvel. \"That`s why the outer layers of my Ashland Attire are of tightly-woven kresh fiber that just sheds ash and soot, so you can look like a lord even in an ash storm!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"With the growth of Balmora, sport hunting in Morrowind has a new capital,\" says designer Arvel. \"Whether you`re pursuing nix-oxen or hunting hive golems, dress for the chase in these luscious leathers!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Telvanni Wizard-Lord Robe',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Wizard-Lords of Great House Telvanni measure themselves by magical power rather than by ostentation or display, so the design of their robes is relatively simple and restrained. Don`t be fooled: these are the garments of powerful sorcerers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Naryu Virian the Morag Tong assassin is nothing if not practical, and her functional, low-profile leather armor provides vital protection without compromising her agile acrobatics.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Nord stevedores who work the docks below the great stone arch of Solitude have a style all their own,\" says Jork the Tailor-Thane of Windhelm. \"They take what they like from travelers of Tamriel and make it their own. Now you can, too!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Egg-Sister Bias-Cut Casual Wear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Simple yet stylish, most advantageous for displaying one`s tattoos and markings,\" says Jaxa-Kel, who found these designs by her relative, the elusive Hermit, at a clothiers` bench near some Barsaebic ruins in Shadowfen.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Lizardly Four-Fabric Skirt Set',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Hermit presents the latest in silky swamp chic,\" says Jaxa-Kel, \"combining flax, feathers, alit-scales, and spun dank-cotton in contrasting layers of chevrons and lightning. So lizardly!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Corset of kagouti-leather, full skirt of dank-cotton, beaded-shell vambraces and bird-skull pauldrons: everything a Xanmeer Doyen needs when welcoming worshipers into the Arboreal Reverie. The Hermit`s outdone itself this time,\" says Jaxa-Kel.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Do you like to keep to the shadows, yet long for a striking look of your own? Any admirer of the Prince of Night and Darkness will appreciate this eye-catching costume.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"We Nords are a people unafraid of getting our hands dirty,\" says Jork the Tailor-Thane. \"We like our clothes to be practical, yet stylish at the same time. My Bleakrock Housecarl Dress is a prime example!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bardic Tavern-Singer`s Dress',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Whether you`re belting out `Ragnar the Red` in the tavern, or just down there for the Loredas evening dance, all eyes will be on you in this free-swinging layered dress!\" —Jork the Tailor-Thane',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"We Nords tend to be an informal people at most times, but when a Jarl sits to decide a legal case, it`s important that our system of law be honored with the proper attire!\" —Jork, the Tailor-Thane of Windhelm',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Rawhide-Laced Riften Jerkin',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Jork the Tailor-Thane says, \"Summer may be short in Riften, but when it finally comes the Nords greet it with open arms. And how better than in this patterned sleeveless jerkin, accented with rawhide laces?\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'New Moons Cross-Sash Robe',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Praxis mandates silk shirtings when attending our weekly Ancestral Homage ceremonies,\" says designer Estinwe of Shimmerene, \"Show pride in your heritage with this shimmering update of a classic, time-tested pattern.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'No one has more respect for their Ceremoniarchy and its functionaries than the High Elves: dignity and a high self-regard are the watchwords of an Altmeri Reeve. This outfit represents the Summerset administrator in all his glory!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Made Wolfshead',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Queen`s-Eye Spymaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You wish to maintain a low profile and yet exude competence, sexy coolness, and undeniable predatory intimidation all at once, yes? Then this one advises investing in a Queen`s-Eye Spymaster costume and flipping a coin in the tavern`s dark corner.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Wear the Outfit of the Fire Drakes, those deadly draconic firebrands of the no-holds-barred Battlegrounds!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Forge-Wife`s Impervious Frock',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Look sharp while you hammer out that dagger!\" says Orc-tailor Borzighu. \"Our Forge-Wife`s Frock, spun from non-flammable gray scathecraw fibers, protects you from cinders, soot, hot embers, and even spatters of molten metal. Hot!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As the Wise Woman of your clan, or the Hunt-Wife on ceremonial days, you must project both grace and authority,\" says designer Borzighu the Tidy. \"Count on my gilt-broidered vestment to provide that, and more!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Wear the Outfit of the Pit Daemons, those infernal dirty fighters of the no-holds-barred Battlegrounds!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Wear the Outfit of the Storm Lords, those triumphant tempest terrors of the no-holds-barred Battlegrounds!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Arena Gladiators of Tamriel`s pit-fighting circuit wear armor that exemplifies the sport`s ancient tradition of a fighter`s protection balanced with the crowd appeal of risk. Why else would one wear heavy armor with significant gaps in it?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Deepwoods Pod-Singer Tunic',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Non-Wood Elves might think it strange that Bosmeri Pod-Singers, who magically persuade Valenwood trees to grow into houses, wear clothes entirely made of animal leather and quills, but such is the mandate of the Green Pact.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Noble Clan-Chief',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I found an illustration for this garb in a founder`s journal and made it for our second Proving Festival. I`m pleased with the result!\"—Magnate Feina-Darak',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Rule over the night with deadly elegance in this sleek ensemble of figure-hugging apparel. The long coat clings as close as your own shadow, and every layer flows as freely as arterial spray from your prey. Just take care not to get blood on your ascot.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Established to create an impregnable border between Skyrim and the Reach, Karthald Hold maintains a war footing year-round, and its jarl stands at the ready to leap to the defense of Skyrim in this regal mix of satin and steel.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Swirls of flowing dresses, wafts of floral scents, dazzling lights, stirring music, and more set the stage for the Shimmerene Soiree! Toast to the continued success and prominence of this High Elf city-state in perfect praxis with an equally perfect gown.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Everything you need to brave the wilds of the forest and bring back some hard-won lumber is supplied in this robust kit, so hoist your trusty axe and get to chopping wood!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In the ceaseless wars of Oblivion, there will always be scoundrels. After rooking marks of goods and foes of lives, this rugged, Dremora-style coat lets you slink away, sounding no louder than a whisper.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Gear up in Wood Elf style! Fashioned after the garb of Eveli Sharp-Arrow, this outfit`s supple leather provides protection while still allowing for astounding trick shots and dizzying acrobatics!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I wrapped my body in the kelp and coral of a sea-bound Nereid and frolicked in the tidepools as I did in childhood. All should enjoy the freedom of Nereid attire as I have.\"—Oceanographic Society Director, Vaerwyeana',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Abecean Sea is fraught with dangers, but your mastery of all things nautical and the feel of your scallop-topped leather boots adds a swagger to your step. Dressed like this, even the fiercest pirates will know better than to challenge you at port.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Jakarn is rugged, practical, and dashing. Dressing like him ensures that you never look like you`re trying too hard. His well-tailored clothes always fetch the eyes of tavern beauties and never chafe when riding a stallion into the sunset.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Among the Vinedusk Rangers lurks an even more dangerous force: assassin-scouts who move quietly through forests, dealing with any who pose a threat. Sometimes called \"tree ghosts,\" they wear custom-made gear that works with their preferred combat styles.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sailor-at-Arms',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'High Isle seafarers often take posts on escort ships, hoping to hone their martial skills and slake their thirst for combat on the open seas. If that describes you, this Breton-designed garb should serve you well!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This exquisite garb was created in honor of Almalexia`s gentle grace and leadership over the centuries since Red Mountain. A devotional surrogate often wears this attire during the days-long observation called the Fast of Forebearance.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Feeling puny? Small? Afraid? Do what I do! Wear your Daedroth apparel and snarl at everyone you meet. No, you can`t have my garb! But I can make you some … for a price.\"—Jester-Apprentice Xat-Xot',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sing, dance, and engage in other artistic pursuits while wearing this Dibella-inspired ensemble. Let the influence of the Goddess of Beauty, Love, and Affection enchant your senses while you spark creativity in others by your very presence.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Early merchant-scavengers of the Zainab Tribe collected Dwarven pieces they found in nearby ruins. Instead of adding them to their wares, though, they worked the pieces into exploration garb, hoping for better protection against Dwarven constructs.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Fleet of foot though wolves may be, the wind moves faster. It flows into places even insects cannot reach. Thus the Skaal witch who masterfully calls upon it gains the title of Windcaller, Blessed of the All-Maker.\"—Skaal Shaman Rik',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Don`t get me wrong, robes are wonderful. But in the field I need something more form-fitting and practical. Plus these boots are magnificent. And the detail on the buckle! Delightful!\"—Mage Adelle Montagne',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally designed for High King Emeric himself, this outfit features high-quality silks and fabrics, granting the wearer a chance to pass like a king through the streets of Wayrest.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Change cannot be denied. Yet some wish to thwart it, finding comfort in stasis. In stagnation. These I seek out in the way of seers so that ku-vastei may deal with them. Once they clear the path, needed change occurs.\"—Claw Seer Deelith-Xul',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Elven Hero',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume pays a 10-Year tribute to our legendary High Elven hero of the Aldmeri Dominion. Honor this nameless mage by adopting their epic appearance, updated with touches of gold and ivory for the occasion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Nord Hero',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume pays a 10-Year tribute to our legendary Nord hero of the Ebonheart Pact. Honor this nameless warrior by adopting their ferocious appearance, updated with touches of gold and ivory for the occasion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Breton Hero',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This costume pays a 10-Year tribute to our legendary Breton hero of the Daggerfall Covenant. Honor this nameless rogue by adopting their intimidating outfit, updated with touches of gold and ivory for the occasion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Honor Sanguine with enthusiasm and vigor by dancing the night away in this scarlet-adorned outfit.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sewn by the faithful at the Benevolence of Mara cathedral in the Imperial City. These finely stitched frocks robe Mara`s scholar-priests-in-exile and any new adherents they train to the priesthood.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Loose-fitting garb worn by the band of pirates known as the Sea Drakes, who plagued the waters around Stros M`kai.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sea-soaked armor worn by members of Captain Blackheart`s tyrannical crew out of Bangkorai.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Well-fitted armor from Imperial troops deployed to Satakalaaam.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Dark-hued garments worn by the Midnight Union, a smuggling operation out of Stormhaven.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Battle-tested armor worn by Imperial legionaries assigned to Hallin`s Stand.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Well-worn armor used by mercenaries stationed in Phaer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Swift-Winds Sailor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Sturdy fabric and leather. Dwemer-crafted metal to protect the shoulders and wrists. Oh, and pouches and scroll-holders. That`s what you need to be a proper delver of lost and forgotten ruins.\"—Raynor Vanos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A full body marking that emulates a near-complete second set of scaley-skinned armor.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Croco-Spots',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ink-Blot Scales',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Red-Gold Serpent Scales',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silver-Black Serpent Scales',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bear-Claw Scars',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Heart-Cross Scars',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Broad Half-Body Smearing',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Limb-Bands',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Triple-Ink Chest Wings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black-Eared Puma',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wild-Eyed Wolf Chest',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Open-Front Dense Swirls',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Broad Half-Body Ember Smear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Deep Dark Red-Trim Gorget',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Warrior-Poet Body Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Decorate your epidermis with writhing, sinuous, barbed fingers of mystic energy evoking the imagery associated with Lord Vivec, Tribune and Warrior-Poet of Morrowind!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some say the Mundus is naught but a great Mechanism, and we are but animunculi, like Dwarven automatons, turning like gears in some universal clockwork. But some mortals are just motorheads, you know? These machine-inspired body markings are for them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This design symbolizing the intertwining of all life forms is popular with wyresses, Wardens, Y`ffre-worshipers, and all those who feel a special connection with Nature in Tamriel.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Eagle: symbol of the Aldmeri Dominion and totem of the High Elves, expressing their soaring ambition to be pre-eminent in whatever they choose to pursue. This flurry of eagle feathers displays one`s allegiance to that ideal.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those who`ve run afoul of the Followers of the Manbeast, Lord Hircine, may bear the crimson scars of their encounter for the rest of their lives. Badge of honor? Symbol of devotion? Trophy of a battle well-fought? That`s for you to judge.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Chalk Body Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful body daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in sharp white chalk dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Woad Body Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful body daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful blue woad dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Algae Body Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful body daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful green algae dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Yolk Body Tattoo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cheerful body daubings in the Bright-Throat style, in colorful hackwing egg-yolk dye.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Blood Body Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the fierce Dead-Water tribe goes to a formal declaration of conflict, the warriors daub themselves with red dye that resembles smears of blood.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Seeking to show your devotion to Peryite? These Dragon-shaped stains do just that! They`re best paired with a cough or other visible illness.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"With these markings, it is as if you take the power of the Dragon within you, and let the smoke of its flames conceal you. Whether this is true is now up to you, yes?\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Take the strength of those Dragons you`ve slain with your killing dance into your physical form, melding it with your mind to grow in your purpose. These markings? They represent this purpose.\" —Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'So many Dragons have died at your hands that the smell of Dragon blood has soaked into your very dreams. With great skill, the artist-adept has given you markings that reflect your experience, making them glow with an emerald hue.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After a tattooed Dragon Hunter has killed enough Dragons, an artist-adept adds to the markings, causing the color of its glow to shift to a golden hue.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The darkness within you should be acknowledged, yes? With you, I see it as wings taking you through times of Dark Moons into brighter times. Let us get to work so that you can better embrace this journey.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Do nothing halfway. That`s what Balorgh would say. So, yeah, if you`re gonna mark your victories in ink? I say go for the full-body treatment. So would Balorgh.\"—Yarzurgakh',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When pushed, your white-hot rage breaks free of the icy cage you set around it, smashing your foes. Warn others of your wrathful inclinations with these markings.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You`ve found what you`re looking for in the Cult of the New Moon. And you want everyone to know whose side you`re on. Let the flame symbology of this eye-catching tattoo show them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Your body knows much it doesn`t tell. With artistry, we can call forth the First Cat`s Pride so that you may guide others in Alkosh`s path. They will see the golden fire on your body and follow.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some ruin explorers calling themselves Gloomlurkers mark themselves with chalky-white line patterns after killing the creature that terrifies them most. You want these markings? Go find a beast worth slaying.\"—Gloor the Glowerer',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/bm_grave-plunderer.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Bloodrune-marked Draugrkin graverobbers pride themselves on surviving and thriving in the deadliest tombs. Those who best them in combat have a chance to gain their distinctive red markings.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A Skald is more than a musician. A song more than sound. Let this ink dance around your form and write the music of your soul upon the canvas of your skin. All who look upon you will hear the tempo of your heart.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"You follow in the footsteps of valiant heroes, swearing to prove your bravery so that you may one day enter Sovngarde. Now carry these markings alongside your axe to embody your oath.\"—Gerda Swift-Sword',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"We call those who sprint to the defense of Whiterun `Windracers.` Each wears tattoos that symbolize unity of purpose and fleetness of foot.\"—Gerda Swift-Sword',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Riften Ratway contains many a ne`er-do-well, but that doesn`t trouble you because you`ve earned a high place among this disreputable bunch—and these tattoos prove it! Though blades cross your chest, none in the Ratway of Riften dare cross you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blessed Life-Tree Body Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The brilliant hue of the Ayleid life-tree glows upon those who sought knowledge from the Ayleids—and somehow gained the favor of one of their spirits. While its glow may not light your way in Ayleid ruins, it might win the favor of any lingering ghosts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sul-Xan Prophet Body Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Sul-Xan are renowned for their prowess in battle and their devotion to their cause. The prophet`s red markings are worn only by those who are sworn to ensure the future of the tribe.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sul-Xan Raider Body Markings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Sul-Xan raider oathtaking ceremony includes tracing a marsh-green pattern upon hide and scale. The dye`s acidic scent hints at the level of burning pain involved in this exaltation of chaos.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I proudly displayed my rubyfire brand while I single-handedly decimated a Dremora regiment at Bellow`s Valley. If I see any Xivilai who have fled the field of battle showing their rubyfire marks, I will remove their flesh in strips!\"—Xalwif',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Xivilai, unlike the regimented Dremora, have no patience for hierarchies. But, with its gold hue and filigree-like detailing, it`s difficult not to think that anyone who bears this pattern isn`t royalty of some kind.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Lord of Revelry`s faithful often decorate each other with sacred, floral-based inks. The result? Beautifully rendered roses that bristle with thorns. This alluring design serves as a reminder of Sanguine`s great gifts: both bliss and agony.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally solid colors, the markings some Ket Keptu wore to signify their status as warrior-smiths later gained a gradient of hues. Scholars claim this occurred as these pre-Alessians furthered their knowledge of ore refinement and tattoo inks.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The whispers of Oblivion slither through the halls of Red Petal Bastion—drawing its guardians ever deeper into the Daedra`s embrace. These once-noble warriors forsook their oaths to pursue dark artifacts—but remain forever marked by their choice.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Battle-Scarred Body',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'To the druids, the repetition of one braid forming three-sided shapes is a symbol that all three druidic circles share the same goals. A reminder that unity eclipses the differences in how they revere Y`ffre.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Scholar-priests of Skingrad fashioned these triangular markings to call on the knowledge of the God of Wisdom and Logic. Bearers of the markings say that their memory improved after completing the tattoos.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The calm of the netch infuses some folk. Yet their spirit burns bright with playful inner joy. For one such person, I created colorful tattoos inspired by golden, spotted netches I encountered long ago.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I`ve learned that Nord vessels sailing the Sea of Ghosts prefer having a skald on board to lull the spirits haunting those waters into happier memories. These fish-knot markings indicate a master seafaring skald.\"—Sarion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Ooh! Some of the Firesong Circle`s early markings. This design is so colorful. I wish I knew how it transformed over the seasons. But, I`ll never know because some kelp-brained fool recorded our volcanic history on flammable material!\"—Druid Laurel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A stunning veneration of the Tinkerer in traditional Dark Elf style. The artist`s neo-classical interpretation of Tribunal decorative aesthetics is a tribute to ancient-meets-modern sensibilities.\"—Assistant Maren, Library of Vivec',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'There`s always a celebration when a Telvanni spore savant`s first structure reaches maturation. Some retain spore-ink artisans to decorate the architect`s skin with mushrooms and claim the recipient receives visions of future projects during the process.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"On wicked nights when the wind flees grasping limbs, we weep lich-ink onto ourselves. Any who see us in their dreams take on our lich-bone symbols and step into lands of nightmare while sleeping and awake.\"—Nearly illegible snippet from Larul`s Journal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Barra agea ry sou karan—wear lore as your armor. Say these words at a certain Ayleid gate under the Magician`s light, and you may be blessed with light-blue markings reminiscent of that gate`s design. Which gate? Soon I`ll know.\"—Alfarmuth of Eyevea',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those who create structures using fungus often adorn their bodies with ornate markings featuring mushrooms. These mycoturges provide their own mycelial-based inks to the artist for their works of body art.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some Vaermina cultists believe they can morph dreams into reality via an intricate series of rituals. The rites culminate in an incense-shrouded chamber wherein a recipient gains tattoos similar to the group`s favorite Weaver of Dreams statue.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Body Art',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The art on my body reminds me that life flows from the All-Maker. Earth, sun, and water nurture our forests, where wolves fill the air we breathe with their nightly howls. Then life flows back to the All-Maker in an eternal cycle.\"—Skaal Shaman Rik',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The flowing body art of a Solstheim windcaller brings to mind the breezes and gusts of air that accompany them as they travel. Some claim the marks depict their story of self-discovery while walking the path the All-Maker set before them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A tip: don`t leap into every portal you come across. A memorable excursion saw me stepping from one into the middle of the Nibenay Bay. I was drying the pages of my tome for weeks after.\"—Azandar al-Cybiades',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Soulburst was not merely a physical event, but a sundering of all the souls on Nirn. Such a catastrophe had never been felt on this plane before. The survivors were often changed, sometimes bearing an outward reminder of their own soul-deep struggle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When death-sorrow claws at your mind, look within. Reflect on the Sands Behind the Stars and know that, once there, true cats reside in splendor until the Next Pounce.\"—Artist-Adept Aimira',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Night Mother`s countenance is not a warm or comforting thing. Her dark hands reach out from the shadows, born on a nightshade-scented breeze, grasping and searching, until the victim knows the sweet embrace of death.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Bent Dance corrupts all who fall to its ceaseless drumming. The Rajaska are fueled by this corruption, growing as strong as the Ahz-m`Athra that snarls from the Dark Behind the World.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Body Soul-Mark of the Sapiarchs',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stone-Nest Orator Body Paint',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Prince of Pestilence has writ large upon your skin, acolytes! Skeevers, because they snarl in the face of adversity. A bug to symbolize rot and decay. And Peryite in Dragon form, to remind you of the glory of our cause!\"—Priest Blein Brown-Teeth',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'While hard-earned battle scars are highly respected by the Iron Orcs throughout the Dragontail Mountains, commemorative tattoos like these are also a matter of pride. To insult an individual`s tattoo is to question their honor, often on pain of death.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stone-Nest Xanmeer Body Tattoos',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The wisdom of the Builders was in their patience. They did not just shape the Stone, they listened to it. They waited for it to speak its true shape to them, and then they made it so.\"—Hecicla, Xor-Hist',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Soul-Shriven',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Donning this costume gives the wearer the guise of one of the Soul-Shriven, Molag Bal`s slaves in his Oblivion plane of Coldharbour.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dro-m`Athra',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'One who wears this skin adopts the eerie appearance of a dro-m`Athra or Bent Cat, an evil ancestor spirit of the Khajiit.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Proudly display your victory in Mazzatun with this daub of glowing and magically-infused amber plasm!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blood-Forged',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Blood. Nirncrux. Iron. Combined with the unholy rites of the Reachmen at the Bloodroot Forge, the result is a clinker-cracked, glowing-hot skin like no other: the Blood-Forged!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Look like an ever-burning Flame Atronach from Oblivion with the Infernal Epidermis, a smoking-hot skin of fire, ash, and charcoal.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s said that under certain conditions the Maormer, like chameleons, can change the appearance of their skin. Emulate that legendary ability with this blue-scaled Fish Skin.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sable Man-Beast',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bright-Throat Scale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Kaoc! That luridly patterned Scale Skin style worn by the Bright-Throats is far too gaudy. Could a serious person appear in public like that? I think not.\" —Jaxsik-Orrn of the Dead-Water tribe',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Scale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Not to be overly critical, but in my opinion the shadowy Scale Skin of the Dead-Waters is entirely too austere. Though it is, I admit, simple and elegant.\" —Xukas',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I found the shipwreck locked in ice. The crew were all frozen and frostbitten, and I thought they were dead … until they rose, frost-crusted and icy, and picked up their weapons.\" —Aelfrydda of Dawnstar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sunspire Ice-Fire',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The melding of ice and fire might seem out of reach for the average person, but you`re not the average person, are you? Show your mastery of Sunspire`s Ice-Fire by exhibiting it on your body.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Join the ranks of Peryite`s plague-ridden adherents and enjoy all they have to offer, including a diseased appearance!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blood-Drained Thrall',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/skin_opalescent-epidermis.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Shimmer with a variety of hues, taking on the colors of the famed opals of Yokuda, with this skin. Perfect for star-strewn celebrations in Sentinel and beyond.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Do you revel in cataclysmic forces? Is vindication best reflected in ruining all who thwart you? Perhaps you revere the destructive Daedric Prince Mehrunes Dagon. Whatever the case, this ruddy-hued skin reflects your true nature.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Whether afflicted by the Rivenspire blood-curse or some other vile vampiric corruption, the result is the same: Victims transform into ravenous monsters. These creatures know nothing but rage and hunger. Appalling.\"—Nalana, Advisor to House Tamrith',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A life in Namira`s service often brings bleak and horrifying side-effects. Praise Namira, the Lady of Decay and the Great Darkness! With eyes awash in pitch black ichor, you shall see her will fulfilled.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Treasure rests beneath the oily waters in Clockwork City for those with the guts to plumb deeply into its viscous lubricants. Your valiant effort to dredge up valuable scrap gives your skin a slippery, many-hued sheen.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After the Soulburst, mysterious slate-skinned figures appeared in the Imperial City to fight Daedra. Each one has the Red Diamond encrusted upon their torso. To this day, none know where they come from or where they go after each fray.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Varla-Born',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Cold-Flame Epidermis',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Fancy Cold-Flame Atronachs, do you? Their frozen blue flames? That rock-hard physique? Well, now you can make those elements your own! Perfect for when you need to give someone the cold shoulder.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You`d give anything to Mehrunes Dagon. Offerings of destruction. Of blood. Even your life. Already, you`ve earned the crimson-fire brand of his viscerents after feeding your epidermis to him bit by bit. Your devotion is bared to all. Glory to Dagon!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hist-Tsoko',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Hist-Tsoko are the elder Hists. Rarely, they mark one to carry out a sacred task, and we know to provide aid to them. Sometimes we give words. Sometimes goods. Sometimes distance.\"—Attributed to Sap-Speaker Kuzei',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Let the power of the stars wash over you, my friend. Your skin will take on an astral gleam. On hazy nights when constellations grow dim, the Star-Gazers may turn their eyes to you instead!\"—Overheard in Belkarth',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Culanda-Born Skin',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The mossblood imp`s coloration lends itself well to walking undetected among the foliage of Valenwood. But perhaps that`s not what the mages intended given the provenance of the imp. Unintended consequences abound with imp-related projects.\"—Divayth Fyr',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bargain-Marked Skaafin',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Morality is a useless cause with no end other than smug self-satisfaction. Cast that aside and showcase your mischievous nature. You`ll know you`ve succeeded in shirking your former self when your scarred skin pulls tightly across your chest.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The colorful inhabitants of High Isle reefs often act differently when land-dwellers approach. To better swim among the local aquatic life, druids imitate them by imbuing their skin with gorgeous blues and greens. Care to try it?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Druid chants drift through the air as one of their number drinks deeply of the glowwine. Slowly, the alchemy spreads throughout the body and skin, suffusing it with the amaranthine-hued blessing of the God of Song and Forest.\"—Book of the Leaves',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"To teach within the Order of the Claw, one must first pass the Trials of the Ascetic. In one trial, you must meditate without pause while another designs patterns on your skin with henna. Perhaps next time this one shall pass that trial.\"—Kansur-jo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Aether-Tempered Mystic',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sometimes the most beautiful things are those which have shattered and been pieced back together. Bear your cracks proudly—they are the hard-won trophies of all the things that could not break you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Nothing brings peace like a glass of wine and a little dancing! Under the skin, everyone belongs to Sanguine! We just bring that to the surface.\"—Ree-Jaa, Sanguine Disciple',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'World-Eater`s Flame',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Forged in the crucible of combat? Show the world by taking on this blade-sharp mantle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Take on the bird-beast`s plumage in the name of Tava and Diagna. Listen well to the song of wind and sword before calling upon it in battle.\"—An inscription found near the Battle of Six Hands',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A commander must project confidence and mastery, or no one will want to obey her orders. Behave as if you`re the one making the rules, not following them. Walk like you own the place, and stand like an Emperor.\" —Magus-General Septima Tharn',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"If you`re going to sneak, for the love of Tava don`t do it half-heartedly. Hide! Be furtive! Lurk like you mean it! Because I`m done bailing you out of the Abah`s Watch lock-up.\" —Zeira of the Thieves Guild',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"We have one rule that governs the actions of every member of House Telvanni—there are no rules. We are ambitious, curious, devious, and, yes, power-hungry. For the mage with the most power wins, and the winner is always right.\"—Magister Gothren',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As a Treasure Hunter, forever poking around in shadowy nooks and crannies for loose gems, lost journals, and hidden levers, what could be more important to you than your trusty ever-burning torch? Never again be lost in the dark without it!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You`ve braved dangerous waters and seedy back-alleys. Now, on land or sea, your telltale swagger marks you as someone who`s comfortable in all manner of deadly environments!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Liven up Tamriel with your rakish lunacy—and keep people on their toes with your dagger-sharp wit. Plus actual daggers. Or hammers for those dullards who don`t get the jest.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The dreadguards are the armor-clad shock troops of Molag Bal—utterly loyal, fearless, and bereft of the pedantic attitudes of the lesser Dremora-kyn.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A Pumpkin Spectre is like a horrific figure from a skooma-induced nightmare! And with this costume, the wearer can take on the semblance of these dread monsters.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Barons-Who-Move-Like-This are paragons of the martial arts styles of Oblivion. They are also psycho-magical projections from the mind of Daedric Demiprince Fa-Nuit-Hen, his concept of perfect masters of combat.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dread Anka-Ra',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When Emperor Tarish-Zi returned out of the mists of the past, his ancient warriors rose from the dead to serve him as the stony Anka-Ra, undead that seemed hewn from rock itself. …It could be a good look for you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wraith-of-Crows',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Pay homage to Nocturnal the Night Mistress by assuming the appearance of her horrific half-bird servant!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Befriend your fellow woodland creatures as you dance under the forest`s boughs, swaying gracefully in the guise of a sylvan-born spriggan, and unleash nature`s fury on those who intrude upon the Green.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The quiet desolation of snow-laden forests instills a sense of undisturbed peace. Take on the aspect of stoic winter spriggans that preserve this unmolested tranquility.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Gather the power of Daedric energies within you, then explode with lightning in the form of a cobalt-blue Incarnate. Channeling the power of a tidal wave, you`ll make quite an impact on your friends.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Scholars of the topic once gathered to re-enact the battle between Pelinal Whitestrake and Umaril the Ayleid sorcerer-king. Thankfully, their well-crafted illusion magics live on to this day. Care to daunt the dauntless by donning it?\"—Stephen Surilie',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Spin an illusion to appear as a scintillating glass Atronach, native of the realm of Mirrormoor. Those razor-sharp edges reflect  how dangerous you truly are.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Harvest`s reaping brings out all sorts of ill-omened beings. I avoid that nonsense by looking like a scarecrow spectre animated by amethyst flames. An illusion, yes, but yours if you can handle the terror you`ll inflict.\"—Othreloth Hlaalo, Illusionist',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'World-Eater`s Living Armor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Alduin`s infamous hunger lends a razor-sharp edge to this smoldering polymorph. His shadowy scales will hold your enemies in rapt horror, while you invoke his scorching rage on all who oppose you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Volley of the World-Eater',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Applies to The Unblinking Eye, The Languid Eye, and The Tide-King`s Gaze. Select in Skills menu.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Applies to Caltrops, Anti-Cavalry Caltrops, and Razor Caltrops. Select in Skills menu.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Applies to Soul Trap, Consuming Trap, and Soul-Splitting Trap. Select in Skills menu.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Tome-Bearer`s Inspiration, Dawn Orange',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In Sentinel, the best way to hide out in plain sight is with a private room in the Sisters of the Sands, the town`s largest inn. It also has the best food in the city, and is the place King Fahara`jad sends to for take-out.\nRoom is too small for Dueling.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even if you don`t personally have a taste for the famous fire-pit dancing at the Flaming Nix, you have to admit it adds a certain cachet to having a room there. Not to mention an unusual fragrance.\nRoom is too small for Dueling.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'For the city-loving Dark Elf, there`s no better choice of residence than the Saint Delyn Penthouse in the heart of Vivec City, on the Waistworks level of the Saint Delyn canton.\nRoom is too small for Dueling.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A perfect graht-oak pod home, grown by a Home Singer from the very roots of Elden Root—compact, comfortable, and convenient to everything. Praise Z`en!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The famous Breton merchant-explorer Captain Margaux hasn`t been seen since her ship the Golden Spriggan sailed off over the horizon into the Sea of Pearls—which makes her house near the docks in Daggerfall available for you!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'All your friends are already nearby in Rawl`kha, yes? Invite them over to have a party at your so-sleek riverside house, with its private garden and over-creek deck. Much sweetness!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'No one has seen Phrastus the Scholar since his ill-advised return to the Imperial City. He`s probably fine—he must be!—but in the meantime, his walled town house in Elinhir is available on an indefinite basis.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Autumn`s-Gate',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Fine urban living in Windhelm is now available at this commodious town home, which features a lofty main floor, two fireplaces, and a second-floor balcony. Alas, that balcony lacks a railing, which is how Grymharth, after too much mead, came to woe.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"It may be small, but at least it`s gloomy. And if you enjoy beating up on your friends, like I do, it`s right next door to the arena!\" —Goorguk gro-Murtag, Orcish Realtor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'On the coast north of Gnisis, this three-level home in the Redoran \"bug-house\" style comes with a walled courtyard, a nearby dock, and convenient access to the nearby ruins of Ashalmawia and Arkngthunch-Sturdumz.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This elegant walled estate is truly the apogee of Altmeri architecture, including a grand entrance hall, curving double staircases, and a blossom-tree garden with circular reflecting pool.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stay-Moist Mansion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'How does this spacious and comely hilltop manor, so far above the fen, nonetheless stay so delightfully damp? It is a paradox, like life itself. (Don`t miss the upper-story lodging with separate entrance!)',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Gardners were the royal family of Wayrest before every single one of them was carried off by the Knahaten Flu. Which is why the spacious and well-situated Gardner House feels like it`s fit for a king!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'S`ren-ja Manor' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You probably think only the mad masterminds of vast criminal organizations have their own private tropical islands. Well, think again: you, too, could have a hidden hideaway ever-trembling on the verge of volcanic destruction!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Get small to go large: this miniature Snow Globe Home is tiny on the outside but expansive on the inside, proving shrunken real estate is a big bargain! And to make the interior cozier, the exterior features an eternally-festive gentle snowfall. Magical!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Pit Fighting promoter Crottus \"Thumbs-Down\" Lycus built this private arena atop the haunted ruins of Molavar because the land was cheap, and what could go wrong? He vanished mysteriously some time ago, and now his unique Arena Home is back on the market.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Khajiit of Elsweyr built this awesome temple as a tribute to the legendary hero, Khunzar-ri. Elsweyr`s greatest champions may assume stewardship of the Hall, but only the most patient and cunning will discover all of its secrets!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Moon-Sugar Meadow',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'With its pillars of skulls, stained glass, and ghostly portals, this abode can accommodate even the most tormented soul. Take advantage of its open layout to set up large-scale rituals, and use its vaults and lofty balconies for vile experiments.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally built by the Potentate Versidue-Shaie as a retreat from Senchal, this manor contains roomy spaces in which to entertain guests. A terraced area features a flooded aeonstone crater as well as luminescent flora transplanted from Moonlit Cove.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Thunderous waterfalls, an imposing smithy, and a magnificent view of the Great Bay make this brisk coastal village the perfect refuge for adventurers seeking a rugged Orcish lifestyle. |cFFFFFFIncludes a built-in blacksmithing station.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Many lived within Solitude`s coveted Proudspire Manor over the years, but its last owner vanished, leaving its spacious living quarters empty—and available. Shelter yourself from the cold within this multi-room landmark in the heart of Solitude.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Before working arcane miracles on Eyevea and the College of Winterhold, the great mage Shalidor experimented with pocket realms of Oblivion. One domain, his Shrouded Realm, features Nord-style towers on arboreal terrain that floats in a wondrous sky.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The recently abandoned Sheogorath shrine that locals call Assalkushalit features a statue to the Mad God within its stony hall. Whether you revere this Daedric Prince or want a home nestled in Red Mountain, this portal-ridden sanctuary can be yours!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ancient pillars along the Abecean Sea mark the site of once-soaring Ayleid architecture. Though none know the original purpose of these structures, some claim that soaking in the retreat`s indoor crystal pool heals the spirit.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Forged in the fires of the Deadlands, this lava-ringed plateau features a stunning view of Daedric landmarks and a solid foundation on which to build your very own Daedric dwelling. Live dangerously within the realm controlled by Prince Mehrunes Dagon!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once the home of an eccentric merchant-collector, this sumptuous manor possesses a view framed by one of Fargrave`s otherworldly skeletons plus offers easy access to all the amenities and exotic goods this city provides.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Variously held by both House Dufort and Mornard, this stately manor near the edge of Gonfalon Bay is now available to the adventurer-about-town. It commands a majestic view of the water and provides easy access to the jewel of High Isle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Enjoy sea-based living on the Fair Winds, a spacious galleon hailing from the Systres Isles. You have a bevy of travel options a mere spin of the ship`s wheel away, with ports of call in Vulkhel Guard, Davon`s Watch, and Daggerfall. Just watch for ornaugs!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Years ago, Tribunal priests requested a Necrom-based residence for an emissary and their staff. Today, this expansive home with scenic terraces is privately owned and seeks a caretaker—perhaps you—until an emissary of the Three needs it again.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A winding maze dominates the grounds of this twilight-enshrouded estate, creating endless opportunities to perplex visitors. The visceral awe evoked by Nocturnal`s Evergloam skies provides an exquisite contrast to the spacious, Summerset-inspired home.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sword-Singer`s Redoubt',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some claim the truest treasure in this former Sword-Singer stronghold glitters below ground in the form of cool, clear water. After the retreat of the Sword-Singers, enterprising merchants set up markets here for wealthy clients. Perhaps you will too?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Designed by a mycoturge for a now-missing arcanist, this Telvanni-style residence showcases gorgeous views. Both magical and mundane access to a sizable workshop and a cozy living space allow for uninterrupted research and rejuvenating rest, respectively.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Breezes carry verdant scents from the nearby jungle to caress the sand gardens in this former Desert Wind adeptorium. Though no longer a site of Khajiit practicing a dual-sword technique, this riverside location serves well as a meditative getaway.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Merryvine`s wines once rivaled those of the nearby Valente Vineyard, but misfortune sent its former owner fleeing. This sun-kissed estate features fertile grapevines, a house suitable for entertaining, and facilities that would please any vintner.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Scintillating islands and skeletons of long-forgotten beasts float amid Mirrormoor`s luminous skies. Enterprising architects, step through a shattered mirror portal in Fargrave and finesse this osseous mass into a dazzling dimensional home.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once a relaxing getaway for Corelanyan nobles, this elegant retreat features an outdoor pool along the shore, indoor steam baths, and spacious facilities that allow even the most battle-worn adventurer to treat themselves.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'An entertainer`s delight! Plays, recitals, and more once filled the stage in this Ayleid theater—all dedicated to Merid-Nunda, the Bright One. Tucked away in the Colored Rooms, this opulent venue awaits its next riveting performance and adoring patrons.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Experience all of Y`ffre`s seasons in a single day! This estate blends a Druid-crafted four-season garden and the beauty of a Breton`s noble villa. Grab a trowel and start making this garden getaway your own!',
