esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This free-spirited merchant is happy to join your adventures and take excess loot off your hands; however, Cyrodiil and Battlegrounds are too bloody for her liking.\n\nWhen summoned, she will purchase any non-stolen goods you or your groupmates offer her.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This Alfiq merchant buys your non-stolen wares as often as you need him to—but not in Cyrodiil or Battlegrounds, which Fezez avoids due to \"considerations of extreme danger.\"\n\nWhen summoned, his services can be used by you and your groupmates.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This Blackfeather Court merchant can relieve you of shiny, non-illicit burdens. She avoids Cyrodiil or Battlegrounds, describing them as \"unprofitable\" and \"full of fat-legged giants.\"\n\nWhen summoned, her services can be used by you and your groupmates.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Summoned from the fourth Sinus of Takubar, Hoarfrost will convey your goods (or the goods of your groupmates) to the cold-flame pits of Oblivion in exchange for mortal coins.\n\nAncient bindings prevent them from appearing in Cyrodiil or Battlegrounds.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sharp-as-Night',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sharp-as-Night is more than a mysterious mercenary with a forgotten past. With your help, he`s learning what it means to look out for others. Call this companion to your side when you need to get the job done with a hardened survivalist watching your back.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Azandar al-Cybiades',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Azandar al-Cybiades has always known he was meant for greatness. Every twist and turn on his path to arcanist power was done with clear eyes and a convivial attitude. Call this companion to your side and undertake an eldritch adventure into the unknown!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Zerith-var',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The world has changed much since his day. Zerith-var, necromancer of the Order of the Hidden Moon, knows he has been sent to this time for a reason. Call your tamiit to your side to seek Azurah`s twilight path together.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A well-trained raptor.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mezha-dro`s Sealing Amulet',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A strange amulet used by Mezha-dro to seal tears in Oblivion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sword-Swallower`s Blade',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Fire-Breather`s Torches',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Quite a harmless, but earnest, display of largesse and lung capacity - feel free to spew fire everywhere!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wild Hunt Leaf-Dance Aura',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Turns your world black-and-white, and summons a ghost that everyone can see. NOT IN USE',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This rough-hewn crystal star pulses with brilliant Daedric energy—using it produces a dazzling tribute to Azura.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This enables its possessor to temporarily assume the appearance of wearing a suit of Dwemervamidium, or steam-assisted semi-mechanized heavy Dwarven armor. It`s genuinely awe-inspiring, albeit only briefly.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Command a magically-murderous crow to crash down upon your enemies in a suicide strike.\n\n|cFFFFFFThis Memento is used on other players.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'There`s angry, and then there`s conjuring-an-erupting-volcano-in-the-floor angry.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'With this memento, for just a moment, you conjure the awe-inspiring illusion of the rise of a dreadful Bone Dragon.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When you use this brief Psijic illusory enchantment, you seem to be scrying a globe of the night sky! The appearance of this relic is based on the Order`s researches into the entirely UN-celestial Abyssal Pearls.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Gourd-Gallows Stump',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Rind-Renewing Pumpkin',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Murkmire Grave-Stake',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Like most adventurers, you`re probably worried that no one will remember you when you`re gone. Create your own momentary memorial with the Murkmire Grave-Stake! Because you deserve it, hero.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Apple-Bobbing Cauldron',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Vossa-satl',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This memento enables one to play the bizarre Argonian vossa-satl, or Frog-Pipes. Party in the swamp!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Sometimes you just need to chill out. This blizzard-creating memento can help with that!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wooden Grave-Stake',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The artists of Black Heights honor their lives through their paintings on the Wall of Life. Now, to commemorate their practices, you can paint a tree in mid-air.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Fungimancer`s Prayer-Beads',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When invoked, you can use these prayer-beads to form a circle of glowing mushrooms around you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When looking for your dig site, use your telescope—unless you love baking under the desert sun or freezing your arse off in snow-covered valleys for weeks on end because you chose to eyeball it instead.\"—Ugron gro-Thumog, Antiquarian',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Full-Scale Golden Anvil Replica',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Never again suffer the indignities of a weed-filled garden! This potent phial contains a defoliating decoction that hastily rids you of any and all corrupting creepers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Use this gem to create the illusion of a ruby-hued incarnate and direct its movements with your own! It`s sure to startle even the most unflinching spectator.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You haven`t lived until you`ve thrown yourself into a Riften-style leafpile. Start by making the pile. Then throw yourself into it. Praise Kyne!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When you have a barrel full of blades nearby, you`ll never be caught flat-footed!\"—Old Fighters Guild Motto',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The nacreous waters of the Bowl of the Hunt await the bone`s holder. Look deeply. Beyond your skin. Feel it? The hunt howls through blood and bone and sinew. Now, sing your wolf-song to begin your journey as one of Hircine`s chosen.\"—Witchmother Gretis',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Share a delightful stack of gooey-sweet baked goods with your best friends. Or taunt your worst enemies with them—you have sweetrolls and they have none!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'No amount of time spent in the Infinite Archive can prepare you for that moment when you pick up an everyday item and suddenly change into a murder-glass monstrosity!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This knife is the greatest of all time! Sharp, well-balanced, keeps its edge, changes you into a goat. And around here, nobody notices extra goats.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Aether-Traveled Varla Stone',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A simple spell using petals from the Rose-of-Archon transforms a well-crafted veil into something magical.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Seed-Heavy Hist Bulb',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A hardy, well-rounded, and dependable beast.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This energetic mount is well-liked by battlefield scouts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Impetuous and fierce, this all-purpose Imperial steed yields only to a capable master.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A rare, highly sought cross between a midnight steed and a Skyrim ice-horse.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Staunch and vigorous, this patterned war-horse is known for its courage and tenacity.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These chargers are descended from the great gray war-horses of the Ra Gada.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Horse',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'With its equine psyche stolen by Daedric magic, the mind-shriven horse is a docile yet terrifying mount.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Behold the Skeletal Horse! Mortal races are not the only creatures that can be re-animated by necromancers. The best part: no need to muck out the stable.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Mannimarco`s Order of the Black Worm must be responsible for the re-animated Zombie Horse, as it was first seen in Cyrodiil as a Worm Anchorite`s mount.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Wood Elves invoke the Wild Hunt, creatures forget their Y`ffre-taught shapes and shift into unnatural forms. Such are the Wild Hunt Horses, mounts that occupy a space between flora and fauna.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Empire of Cyrodiil was at its height, the Imperial Legion Cavalry rode these chalk-white chargers into battle beneath the red diamond banner. \n|cFFFFFF\nRiding Skill does not affect this mount`s appearance.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though Dwemer constructs are made mostly of so-called Dwarven Metal, some rare animunculi have parts forged from a super-hard whitish alloy known to blacksmiths as Dwarven Adamant. It`s one of the rarest materials on Nirn.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though most ancient Dwemer automata are constructed primarily of the so-called Dwarven Metal some rare and special animunculus mounts wear a shell of other materials, such as Ebony. The resulting Ebon Dwarven Horse is an especially durable vamidium.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A horse-shaped Dwarven mount constructed of Ebony, Adamant, Dwarven Metal, and Glass? Sure, why not? The Dwemer could build almost anything, and seemed determined to prove it.\" —Herebane, Nord \"Scholar of the Vanished\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_horse_shadow-ghost.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_horse_m-witchkn.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_horse_plague-husk.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'White-Gold Imperial Courser^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Created after years of extensive breeding, the White-Gold Imperial Courser is said to be the most beautiful horse in all of Tamriel. With its almost ethereal beauty, these horses are owned by only the wealthiest riders.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Is that the famed and incredibly-rare creature of legend, the true Unicorn from Hircine`s Oblivion realm of the Hunting Grounds? …Well, no, it`s a horse with a horn attached to its forehead. But the effect—it`s just so magical!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The ancient Nords who came to Skyrim with Ysgramor worshiped animal totems, and adorned their mounts with symbolic hair-knots and hide strips meant to protect their livestock from the frigid climate. These  \"Frostbane\" talismans are still in use today!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Snow-Blanket Sorrel Horse^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This handsome breed of horse is native to the Colovian Highlands of Cyrodiil, and is a common sight from Chorrol to Bruma. The Snow-Blanket Sorrel is known for its intelligence and high spirits.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The thief-god Rajhin is said to have stolen these enchanted purple steeds from somewhere in Oblivion, but when his worshipers are asked where he got them, they just laugh and say, \"Noweyr!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hollowjack Wraith-Lantern Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Conventional wisdom holds that these bizarre and eerie Skull mounts are just horses imbued with a haunting illusory appearance—but some whisper that they aren`t from Tamriel at all, but summoned from the Hollowjack half-world or demiplane.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Rahd-m`Athra',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the dro-m`Athra ride from the Dark Behind the World, they go mounted on these dread steeds: the Rahd-m`Athra! Are they spirits from the Dark Moons, or tangible creatures of evil?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Horse-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Scorching Horse-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"It is hard to start a campfire in the damps of the deep marsh, yes? Not when you have a Scorching Horse-Lizard! With one of these as your mount, you will never again have to eat cold eel stew!\" —Ukaspa, Stablemaster of Lilmoth',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Stolid, careful, sturdy, and long-suffering, the Treasure Hunter`s Horse is resigned to a life of being ridden into crumbling ruins by a reckless master who`s searching for wealth but often finds only danger.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I have been fortunate enough to have personally glimpsed a Solar Horse on an Anequine morning, and I say with conviction that it must be a creature of Magrus, the Cat`s Eye, and no other.\" —Moon-Bishop Hunal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dragonscale Barded War-Horse',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Dragons are a pain in the tailbones, yes? But their scales make such superb steed armor! The Dragonscale Barded War-Horse may be the sharpest mount this one has ever seen!\" — Master Groom Zarbi`dahuz',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Daggerfall Dapple is a hardy horse breed that comes from the Farwatch region of Glenumbra between Daggerfall and Camlorn. Known for its endurance, it`s a favorite of long-distance riders.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The well-traveled Baandari Pedlars lend their style to this horse`s tack, creating a look any lover of rich hues would die for. Today it can be yours—with no need to die!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As the Dragon threat spreads, the need for veteran Dragon Hunters increases. These gold-barded horses can help you reach your prey quickly.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_coalsmokeforgehorse-.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dread-Aurelian Charger^N',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'With their glowing yellow eyes and flashy golden barding, these veteran steeds serve their Dragon-slaying riders with nobility and style. Be sure to keep some sugar cubes handy—they have a taste for sweets that rivals the Khajiit!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Jade-Crown Dragonslayer Horse',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wasseek Horse-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Only the Wasseek-haleel would breed such a colorful and sweet-natured horse-lizard. Ideal for those times when you`re wandering through Murkmire, looking for trouble to quash.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Eats-All-Bugs' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_winterbloom-warmblood.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hunters riding these valiant steeds are often the first on the scene of a Dragon attack. With its ornate, jade-accented barding, and its fierce loyalty to its rider, this steed is a must-have for any veteran Dragon Hunter.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Icereach Wicker-Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Glorious and deadly. Majestic and haunting. This well-armored steed serves its master faithfully, though its nightmarish appearance once inspired rumors of a ghoulish nature in the area around Cragwallow.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'With barding featuring Whiterun`s heraldry, this indomitable horse remains sure-footed in the snowy mountains of Skyrim and beyond. Majestic!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Label your fact from fiction, Mirannah! `The barding on Potentate horses shimmers due to a geas of loyalty Versidue-Shaie instilled in the materials.` No. It`s simply magic. But 2E 5 for their first use? Feasible.\"—Honorata Ancrus, Eyevea',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ride like the wind on this fleet and sure-footed horse! A favorite of stablemasters, Whiterun Windsteeds possess steady temperaments and gentle gaits, making them the perfect first mount for any rider.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Welkynd-Born Courser',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though the Dragon Maarselok`s blue-limned scourge illuminates this conjured steed, never fear! The magic that summoned it contains the blight, keeping the Green safe—but given its penchant for biting, tip the stablemaster extra for its keep.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The magic-wielding knights of Zenithar`s Crucible prize these molten steeds above all else—even their arms and armor! To this day, no force has weathered the charge of an Iron destrier.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These black-and-gold barded destriers carry their riders with distinction as they sweep across Cyrodiil, serving as but one symbol of goals and experiences their dauntless combatants share. \n\n|cFFFFFFRiding Skill does not affect this mount`s appearance.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The envy of treasure-seekers throughout Tamriel, this sure-footed steed serves as both a sturdy companion and an enduring reminder of what fellowship and camaraderie can achieve.\n\n|cFFFFFFRiding Skill does not affect this mount`s appearance.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bonfire Wicker-Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Nebulous Star-Born Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The hues on these reefborn steeds—wondrous, yes? Instead of flowing manes on these so-called equines, colorful coral grew. Just don`t try to feed them apples. They prefer to feed on algal blooms.\"—Saissula, Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Born Guardian Horse',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'All Star-Born horses are children of the Steed. Impatient and in a rush, these creatures are difficult to tame. Any time spent earning their trust is always recovered the second they`re allowed to canter down an open road.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The day a Stonelore druid thundered in on this frightful sea-birthed horse, well … let`s just say I`m glad I recognized Druid Dolvasie on top. Her ferocious expression will haunt my nightmares—as will this steed.\"—Squire Hareld, Oaken Order',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Su-Zahleel Horse-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Lizard-steeds are a gift from the Hist. They have dependable backs and dry scales. You know, we only realized how entwined our roots were when we trekked back from Mazzatun. These beasts kept us off our aching feet.\"—Skeexalttul, Su-Zahleel Ambassador',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Sunset-in-Scales' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Though these fellows work the tilt-yard like a dream, they`re trained to the field, too. You never know when you`ll need a finely barded steed to get you across those fancy sunflower fields you see around High Isle.\"—Perien Jerrick, Castle Navire',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The scent of flowers precedes this cream-colored steed`s arrival. White-and-merlot barding features the grinning silver-and-gold visage of Sanguine, Lord of Revelry. Will you let the promise made by its illusory roses and wine entice you into merriment?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Horse',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The harmony of the All-Maker dwells within the chest of this steed. It breathes in the breath and breathes out the wind. In its wake does the earth move, the waters flow, and the sun shine.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The people of Riverhold have bred these horses for generations. The result is a line of bright-eyed and faithful steeds, eager to please with their rich chestnut coat. On the road, few horses are steadier or more reliable.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Lion Guard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Kyne-Blessed Thundersnow Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Leopard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Clouded Senche-Leopard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Senche-Panther',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Lioness',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Striped Senche-Tiger',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A semi-domesticated version of the wild senche-tiger, this distant relative of the Khajiit has been bred for size and manageability.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Ratter-do' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Skeletal Senche may be the most fearsome of all feline mounts. Expertly re-animated, even in undead form it retains all the lithe strength it possessed in life.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dro-m`Athra Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Senche-shaped dro-m`Athra are known to the Twilight Cantors as the sar-m`Athra, but everyone else just calls these eerie and uncanny mounts the Dro-m`Athra Senche.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Soul-Eater' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pride-King Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Pride-King Lions are the top predators on the savannahs of Northern Elsweyr. No one but the Khajiit, with their feline intuitions, could have persuaded these proud beasts to serve as mounts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Wild Hunt unravels the shapes Y`ffre established for creatures in the Dawn Era, transforming them into monstrous but vigorous hybrid beasts. Among these, both beautiful and abhorrent, is the Wild Hunt Senche-Mount.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'At the Palace of the Mane near Torval, by tradition the Bi-Lunar Guard are all mounted on matching Black Mane Lions, which are reserved for them alone. So be wary if you ride your Black Mane near Torval, lest you anger the Bi-Lunars!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The legendary preferred mount of Elsweyr`s greatest thieves, the most famous Black Senche-Lion of all was Rajhin`s mount Umbrage, which could both talk and, for brief periods, fly!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Since nearly all Dwemer sites are in northeast Tamriel, where the only large feline is the sabre cat, scholars of Dwarven civilization have long wondered why they chose to make animunculi mounts that resemble the senche-tigers of the south. It`s a mystery!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'There have long been unconfirmed reports of Dwarven Senche vamidiums with key parts made of the extremely rare and super-hard Dwarven Adamant metal. At long last, these reports have been substantiated.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Certain rare Dwarven senche vamidiums are constructed with key mechanical components forged, not of the usual Dwarven metal, but of ebony and ebony-steel alloys.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When considering the Dwarven automaton mounts, the so-called vamidiums, one gets the sense that the Deep Elves were not attempting to replicate nature, but to improve upon it. Case in point: the Vitrine Senche.\" —Thelwe Ghelein, Scholar of the Dwemer',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A night-black senche-tiger with burning paws and flames hissing from its face: this is surely the stuff of evil dreams. The origin of this horrific mount is obscure, but some see the hand of Mehrunes Dagon in it.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_senche_shadow-ghost.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'An oversized breed of black senche-panthers, the Shadowghost Senche is said by the Khajiit to be sacred—or rather unholy—to Namiira the Great Darkness, who sends them as mounts to bear away those who are doomed to die.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_senche_frost-draugr.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'What were senche-tiger mounts doing in ancient Skyrim, and why were their half-frozen bodies mummified beside the Draugr in certain dark Nord catacombs? And why are they rising now, imbued with animating frost magic? The answers are as yet unknown.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Long-held grudges and rage simmer within this skeletal senche—fitting given its supposed origin as a battle steed for Orcs fighting within the Ashen Forge! This mount`s riders gain the utmost respect from Malacath`s adherents.\"—Erisa Moorcroft',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'For centuries the conjurers` standard spell for summoning Flame Atronachs has been Koron`s Peremptory Summons, which is easily modified to change both the duration of the summoned atronach`s binding and its form—for example, into that of a senche-tiger.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'King of the Nightmare Pride, this night-black senche-tiger has burning paws and flames hissing from its face; rumor says Mehrunes Dagon is responsible.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Shadow-Rider Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Creatures of \"Shadow\"—are such things possible? Or is the Shadow-Rider Senche merely a black senche-panther mount wrapped in Illusion spells? Somehow, it just seems too uncanny for that mundane explanation.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Green-Graht Ghost Cat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Cougar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The cliffs and escarpments of east central Elsweyr are the home of the nimble and sure-footed senche-cougars, who prowl the rocks hunting goats and marmots. Inevitably, they`ve been domesticated by their feline cousins the Khajiit.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Noble Riverhold Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The pastoral tribes of northern Anequina need reliable mounts upon which to follow their herds of livestock, and none are more dependable than the prides of senche-lions bred near Riverhold, feline steeds so brave and loyal they`re called \"Noble.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Most inhabitants of Skyrim hate and loathe necromancy, but those Nords who do stoop to raising the dead tend to go all in, wallowing in death and its symbols. It was no doubt such Nord necromancers who bred the skull-faced Death Mask Sabre Cats as mounts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Jaque o` the Hollow haunts Rivenspire during dark Witches Festival nights, and even those who ride senche-tiger mounts may find themselves padding headless through the moonless dark while waving a glowing gourd.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hollowjack Flame-Skull Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Conventional wisdom holds that these bizarre and eerie Skull mounts are just  senche-panthers imbued with a haunting illusory appearance—but some whisper that they aren`t from Tamriel at all, but summoned from the Hollowjack half-world or demiplane.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"More than once I have been asked, `Ukaspa, why are your lizard-steeds shaped like mounts from other parts of Tamriel? Why aren`t your so-very-handsome mounts shaped like, well, lizards?` These are good questions!\" —Ukaspa of Lilmoth',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chilling Senche-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"This Chilling Senche-Lizard is quite rare; it comes from very deep in the swamp, from a tribe said to be dedicated to Frost spells as a means of living longer by living slower. Their Hist tree even drips with icicles (whatever they are)!\" —Ukaspa',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Frost-on-Scales' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sapiarchic Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As the Sub-Sapiarch of Domestic Livestock, I was assigned by Larnatille to breed an appropriate mount for our sages to ride upon when working in the field. I proudly present my result: the loyal and majestic senche-serval!\" —Corderil of Sunhold',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'According to the notebooks of Corvus Direnni, the frost senche-panther may actually be a form of atronach summoned from a plane known as the Fourth Sinus of Takubar. Why it remains in Tamriel where it willingly submits to the orders of mortals is unknown.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Tenmar Senche-Tiger',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Deep in the shadows of the Tenmar Forest, hidden by its camouflaged coat and stealthy stalking, the Senche-Tiger is a nearly invisible jungle predator. Even as a mount, it retains something of the air of mystery it wears in the wild.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some accounts of Meridia`s plane of the Colored Rooms describe a menagerie of light-imbued spectral beasts elevated from Nirn and `purified` by the Lady`s holy light.\" —Sayings of Valasha',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Our distant cousins, the senche-mounts, look so majestic in Dragonscale Bard, like creatures who`ve just stepped out of an ancient wall-frieze in Dune. Perhaps these pesky Dragons have a use after all, yes?\" — Master Groom Zarbi`dahuz',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Clanky-Cat' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Baandari Pedlar Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Prone to rumbles and purrs, the Baandari Pedlar Senche-Lion serves as both a mount and a source of warmth on cold evenings around the campfire. Just watch out for that rasping tongue.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Indigo Senche-Panther',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally bred for a reclusive family in Rivenspire, the Indigo Senche-Panther possesses a distinctive black fur that has a purple sheen. Rumors claim that when left to its own devices, it stalks werewolves for amusement.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Anka-Ra Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A combination of feline agility with the power of a sandstorm makes this mount both a favored and feared battle companion of the eternally loyal Anka-Ra warriors.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blazeborn Senche-lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Born in flame, this senche-lion`s temperament matches its fiery appearance. Those who earn its respect, however, gain a mount that can blaze a path through the darkest shadows.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Verkarth Senche-Lioness',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This sleek and light-hued mount hails from Verkarth, where some warriors drill both night and day to earn the right to train a young one as a battle mount. Now more widely available, you too can add one to your stable.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Plagueborn Senche-Panther',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Riders of these senche-panthers often find their welcomes worn out while in town, but their journeys across wilderness can be strangely trouble-free.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Kynbound Senche-Panther^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Known as steeds of the Dremora, Kynbound Senche-Panthers have found their way into service as mounts for those who have some ties to the Dremora. Perhaps that`s you?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sunspire Champion Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those skilled enough to overcome Sunspire can earn a special variant of the Sunspire Ice-Fire Senche-Lion. With golden armor and gear, this mount shines, reflecting your own adventuring glory.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Volcanic Senche-Panther^M',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Most sorcerers scoff at the idea of imbuing the lumbering frost atronach with feline grace, but when summoned correctly, this frigid senche more than matches its warm-blooded peers in quiet and cunning. Perfect for a hero of your stature!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Shadowcap Cave-Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Khefrem Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'To those living in Hew`s Bane, seeing a spotted senche-serval is an omen of good luck. Some, hoping to gain a constant supply of good fortune, captured and trained several cubs. Now they serve as mounts—good luck indeed to those so blessed with one!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This intimidating horned senche steed wears coal-black barding, making its orange flames stand out in stark contrast. Though none know its origins, the touch of the Deadlands looks to be upon this mount, making it favored by Mehrunes Dagon`s adherents.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Culanda-Born Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"This steed`s glow comes not only from its Culanda-enhanced barding but also from an interaction between it and the animal. Culanda is in its blood—state various Nenalata Ayleid writings—giving this senche envious grace.\"—Beredalmo the Signifier',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pellitine Scorch Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After the Scorch of Senchal and nearby areas, several prides of senche-lions moved into the area. Enterprising and desperate Khajiit trained some of these fearless creatures to saddle, hoping to bolster their forces against deadly Dragons.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"I named these senches Nighthaunts because, I suspect, the cult of Vaermina curiosities I was studying during their creation affected their appearance and intensified their glow. Not their nature. Grim-looking they are, yes, but not evil.\"—Mage Naleldil',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Born from the same wretched forges as Dark Anchors, these ebony-alloy senche atronachs manifest in a burst of soul-searing light when called. Though onlookers may feel as if they`ll never be warm again, some riders claim they feel nothing while mounted.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silver Rose Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Knights of the Silver Rose spent years finding the best felines to rid their fortress of pests and annoyances. Generations later, and these senche-servals can clear out banekin infestations in a single day.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Celestial senches prowl over jagged rocks on surprisingly soft paws for creatures made of Spellscar-like stone. Yes, the Steed constellation is a horse, but how the Warrior didn`t ride a starry senche into battle is beyond me.\"—Madadi, Celestial Scholar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Star-Studded' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"There is madness in all of us, and senches don`t commit to anything half-heartedly. I came across one such mad senche and still bear the scars of its wild attacks. To take one on an adventure, you`d have to be mad as Sheogorath himself!\"—Vi Aspblade',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dunecoat Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Reefborn Senche-Lion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Mages Guild scholars think someone creates these types of senches. With what magic, I don`t know. Maybe some sea-loving druid? Regardless, they`re as fierce as you`d expect for a senche mount.\"—Saissula, Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Born Guardian Senche',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Senches are opinionated creatures, but ones imbued with the confidence of the stars are infinitely more judgmental than their Nirn-born counterparts. Riding one of these across Tamriel is a clear sign that even the stars heed your power.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Piebald Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Ride one of these piebalds for any travel outside Sentinel. They love the heat more than any senche-serval I`ve stabled. Makes me believe the tales of Summerset outcasts raising them out in one of the bandit caves nearby decades ago.\"—Burhan, Stablehand',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Falkreath Riding-Lynx',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"It may be a little biased of us, but predators take longer to earn their horns. I suppose we just want proof that they`re well-trained before we give them another weapon. Still, little Ivy was so proud when she got hers.\"—Druid Celina, Beast Master',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Leaf-Flurry' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ashgray Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Purrs-Like-Thunder' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Oleander Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The artists of Black Heights found a new canvas upon which to share their imagination: senche-servals. The high-quality pigments used on this feline`s fur weather much without causing harm, and artists claim the cats preen as they`re painted.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_alkoshs-blessing-lion.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Golden-Maned Na`dak' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Fredas Senche-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Stink-Eyed Beem' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Snowclaw Senche-Serval',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Frostbreak Tiger-Lynx',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Keep it well-fed and you`ll be fine. It`s a smart beast, it won`t scratch or run off if it knows you`ll give it an easy meal. Just watch your rations on the mountains, though. They`re practically invisible in the snow.\"—Stablehand Skagurn',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Warrior Wave Senche-Cheetah',
esoCollectibleData.php:						'name' => 'Nix-Oxen',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Nix-Ox War-Steed^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It was the warlike Erabenimsun tribe of Ashlanders who first broke the wild Nix-Oxen of Vvardenfell to domestic use, and an ashkhan, the legendary Ashu-Ammu, who first rode one into battle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Lustrous Nix-Ox Fabricant Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Nix-Ox Fabricant Steed^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Programmed for obedience and fabricated for endurance, these synthetic Nix-Ox Steeds are the perfect mounts for ranging out from the Brass Fortress across the dangerous Radius.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Firemoth Nix-Ox',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After arriving on Firemoth Island, the slavers found and trained a flame-hued variant of the nix-ox steed. Its vibrant colors belie its fiery temperament, making it a suitable match for those seeking to ride into the midst of combat.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chyle Seamed Nix-Ox Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'First tamed by the Ahemmusa Ashland tribe, this lighter nix-ox steed only recently gained use by those outside the tribe. In fact, some riders who journeyed through Skyrim`s winter noted that this nix-ox loves jumping around in snow.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dagon Fel Nix-Ox Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some scholars say the eerie blue markings on this nix-ox result from strange energies that once emanated from Mzuleft. Locals claim that no such energies exist these days and immediately speak of the steed`s endurance and adaptability.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Legends claim the Erabenimsun tamed these luminous creatures after Ashu-Ammu rode the first nix-ox into battle. While it`s strange to choose a steed whose glow gives away your position, some warriors delight in added danger before battle.\"—Murdyn Athren',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Berylglow Nix-Ox Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Urshilaku Nix-Ox',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Before these colorful creatures served as mounts for the Urshilaku, their shells were ground up for pigment. Seeing their potential as fast-moving steeds, handlers trained them for scouting missions, often hiding their bright colors with dried mud.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Oasis-Strider Nix-Ox',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Nix-oxen are incredibly adaptable, thriving across Tamriel. This subspecies developed bright markings to attract one another across the heat waves of the desert. Their long legs also allow them to cross the sands easily and stay cool in harsh conditions.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Carnaval Nix-Ox',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The allure of Carnaval is enough to entice even the dourest Dark Elf to celebrate. Done with their characteristic attention to detail, they present the nix-oxen of Vvardenfell in stunning color and gilded saddles, perfect for a night of excess.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Golden Nix-Ox Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The gilded shells of these creatures glow in even the weakest ashfall sunlight. Golden nix-oxen are prized both by merchants seeking to display their prosperity and by worshipers of Akatosh for their beauty.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The robust Green Narsis is the standard mount and dray-beast of central Morrowind.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A sturdy, multi-purpose guar, at home anywhere from swamps to the ashlands.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Root-Foot' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In Black Marsh this mount is called Scales-Seem-Daubed-with-Hist-Sap, but the rest of Tamriel just calls it the Hist Guar. It is the only subspecies of guar known to enjoy music.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_guar_shadow-ghost.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The legend of Jaque o` the Hollow has spread even to the misty realms of eastern Tamriel where the Guar roam the woods and marshes, and during the dark nights of the Witches Festival reptile-riders may also find themselves haunted and headless!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Guar-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some dryskins ask, `Since a Guar is already a swamp reptile mount, why create Lizard-Steeds shaped like Guar? Isn`t that somewhat redundant?` These dryskins are unusually perceptive!\" —Ukaspa of Lilmoth',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This kagouti-shaped frost atronach might just be the last thing an unfortunate apprentice warlock crafted before becoming its first victim. Perhaps you can tame this mount? If not, best have extra healing potions on hand for the inevitable bites.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This fell monstrosity inspired Maestro Efnort of the Bards College to write the poem \"The Red-Eyed Terror of Zthenganaz.\" In truth, this steed most often chooses intimidation and flight tactics over direct confrontation.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Born Guardian Guar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Legends in Fulstrom say that a star-studded guar brought the bastard child of King Vrage to their village one snowy night. No one heard or saw the pair arrive, until a child cried out for warmth. The guar disappeared before dawn.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"These hard-headed creatures might seem empty-minded. Yet, somehow, they keep you alive when you`ve angered the ornaugs. Such is the nature of a loyal mount.\"—Saissula, Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The marshfolk vexed the Unfeathered. `They scatter to fight. But they fear so-named guar. Let us use that.` It took longer to acquire the needed guar than to ready them. May they forever hunt Umaril`s foes.\"—Gandranya`s Journal, Translated',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"None can quench the life-fire blazing in this kagouti`s heart. Night and day, we sing and dance amid magma rivers, fanning the spark of creation. If we`re blessed, the magic takes and one of our number gains a devoted steed for life.\"—My Life Amid Flame',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silver-Limned Guar Charger',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Gin-Lah' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The colors! So bright. Thank Peryite, it doesn`t breathe vile fumes. Well, unless you`ve fed it fungus. Then it has the foulest breath ever. So. Don`t feed it fungus.\"—Yamighu`s New-New Journal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After a drunken wrestling match near Shor`s Stand became a hug-the-pangrit contest, several Nords trained these curiosity-driven creatures to the saddle. Now they happily wander Solstice and beyond, trying out new tasty treats from their doting riders.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This is the stoic, hard-working beast that riders in the wastes of Hammerfell count on to survive. And if things come to a fight, it`s just plain mean.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Most riders consider Black Camels to be creatures of bad luck and misfortune. But if you`re a thief riding off into the night with your ill-gotten gains, you might see things differently.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Bag-o`-Bones' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Altmer wizard Corvus Direnni astounded High King Ar-Azal of Hammerfell by conjuring a Storm Atronach that assumed the form of a horse—but when Ar-Azal tried to stump him by commanding he summon a Storm Atronach Camel, Corvus Direnni instantly did so!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Shock-Hump' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Dwarven Camels are most often found among the ruins of the desert-dwelling Rourken clan of the Dwemer, who left northeast Tamriel and traveled west to found cities in the remote back-country of Hammerfell.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When Peregrine Direnni passed her Master Conjurer test by summoning the first-ever Flame Atronach Camel, her mentor Corvus gave her high marks but was heard to comment, \"Now you`re just showing off.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Hotter-than-Sand' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Perhaps the Atmoran totems and dread-knots sported by the Frostbane Camel actually do help protect it from the bitter cold of Skyrim. Or maybe camels are just too ornery to care.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Camel-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Maybe the Camel-Lizard was created so we heroic Argonian adventurers could travel in arid climes like Anequina—or maybe it was so heroic Khajiiti adventurers could have something to ride in Black Marsh. I don`t know, I just want one.\" —Heem-Jas',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Moss-Spitter' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Anka-Ra Sandcamel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When summoned, this warrior mount of the deathless Anka-Ra mystically amalgamates, drawing sand and strength from the distant Alik`r.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Potentate bought several herds of camels in 2E 25 for delivery to Versidue-Shaie, Mirannah of Gwylim states. `Reman desert pursuit` and `enchanted barding like bear` are also true. Chased by glowing camels—what a sight!\"—Honorata Ancrus, Eyevea',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Famous Redguard conjurer, Rozaba af-Nizhadal, often referred to Iron Atronach Camels as \"glass-treaders.\" Adventurers in Hammerfell still find glass tracks from where the atronach`s scorching feet seared the sand!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Though Iron Orcs ate nearly all these gentle camels, the puissant Elinhir mages took them in, allowing them to flourish. With their flowing gaits and downy fur, the sweet-scented creatures became the mages` steed of choice.\"—Garold Farfly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sword-Singer`s Tufted Camel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pyrodraconic Camel-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Give your obedience to none save the gods of Yokuda. The Far Shores recede from he who leans upon thin-blooded shoulders, scornful of his feeble grasp.\"—Plea for Open Eyes',
esoCollectibleData.php:						'name' => 'Multi-Rider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Dwarven Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Clearly the Dwarves liked to travel in pairs now and again, so they built this two-seated animunculi for that purpose. My partner and I adore using it on market day!\"—Delyna Ulvel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Burnished Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Argent Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ride in style with a close friend or partner on this sturdy Skyrim-bred draft horse! With its pillion saddle crafted from genuine horker leather, this horse possesses strength to take two riders without breaking a sweat.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The first pillion mount in Skingrad came about when two of Rislav`s siblings wished to ride with fewer guards about. `Two guards per horse,` they were told. Thus they created the first battle-hardened pillion mount.\"—Richon Charchere, Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Beware lone roads and moonless nights. Beware the haunted hooves. Beware the burning-coal eyes and the fiery trail that follows each dogged step. Most of all, beware of the path of the steed`s terrible riders.\"—Folk Legends of Tamriel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Double trouble approaches when this pitch-black steed rides into town. With more than enough ill-tidings to go around, this Black Fredas steed is living proof that misery loves company.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Guardian Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Constructed of refurbished Dwarven parts within a fully reconditioned housing, the Duo-Dynamo is the perfect mount for a comfortable, sharable ride.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The inky-black fur of this moose blends into shadows during twilight treks a couple may wish to undertake in secrecy. Since the moose shares no gossip, your secrets remain safe.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Hollowsteel Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Good Neramo studied with the Spidersmith. So a many-legged multi-rider construct seemed a perfect choice: Dwarven chassis meets the design of mages and Khajiit, spun up in Orsinium steel. What would the Dwemer think if they could see it now?\"—Fazudah',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Duo-Dynamo Dungeon Delver Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some say that Hircine meddled with the nature of wolves in a way that made them susceptible to shape-shifting, and from this Daedric interference came both the Werewolf—and the Wild Hunt Wolf. What is the truth of this? Y`ffre knows!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The shining metal known as Dwarven Adamant is an alloy melding ores of unknown origin into the most durable material ever made. Though found in parts of the ultra-rare Adamant Dwarven Wolf, the secret of its forging seems as lost as the Dwemer themselves.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_wolf_cinder-skeletal.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This appears to be a reanimated undead corpse of a wolf mount that was burned to death in some horrific event, and has returned hell-bent on vengeance. An intimidating ride, for sure!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_wolf_shadow-ghost.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"An oversized Flame Atronach Wolf makes for an impressive mount,\" wrote arch-conjurer Corvus Direnni, \"but it`s inconvenient to house such a steed in flammable stables. When I`m not riding mine, I temporarily lodge it in a pocket realm Adjacent Place.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Cold-Flame Atronach Wolf^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After years of conjuring, Peregine Direnni sought a new Daedra to compel to be her mount. She took an immediate liking to the Cold-Flame Atronach, found in the Daedric realm of Takubar. Summoning it in the form of a wolf just added extra flair.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Happy-Pant' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In the rugged badlands of central Hammerfell, even camels struggle to maneuver across the broken terrain. But wolves can go where even camels cannot, so the roving Redguards of the canyon lands have bred the local Painted Wolves into sure-footed mounts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Lord of the Nightmare Pack, this night-black Wolf mount has burning paws and flames hissing from its face and tail; can anyone doubt that its origin must be Mehrunes Dagon`s plane of the Deadlands?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Night winds whisper through the Hollow\nAnd the darknight wolf-pack prowls\nThen your wolf-mount turns to follow\nAnd you ride headless as it howls',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Howl-o-Jack' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hollowjack Daedra-Skull Wolf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Conventional wisdom holds that these bizarre and eerie Skull mounts are just riding wolves imbued with a haunting illusory appearance—but some whisper that they aren`t from Tamriel at all, but summoned from the Hollowjack half-world or demiplane.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wolf-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Almost every stablemaster of the Marsh has fine, scaly lizard mounts available for purchase in various forms, all familiar to dryskins but specifically adapted to deep swamp conditions. So convenient, our lizard-steeds, so scaly and personable!\" —Ukaspa',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Scaly-Wolf' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Venomous Wolf-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Moor-Rover' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'War-Wolf' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Oak-Ember Forge Wolf^N',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A young blacksmith raised a foundling wolf decades ago, thus training the first of the Oak-Ember Forge Wolves as a steed. With its unusual fur pattern, you`re sure to make an impression on those around you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Wolf^N',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"You might think Mind-Shriven Wolves are fragile beasts, but their environment has instilled within them a hidden strength. \"—Warlock Aldaale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Taken from the crime-ridden back streets of Senchal and raised by scavengers, this mount lost an eye while defending its rider from pursuing guards. Now wearing a patch, the Howler is an ideal mount for doers of deadly deeds.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Curdles-Blood' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Varla-Born Wolf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The eerie glow of those born from Varla-touched wolves, as the Nenalata called them, intensifies when a rider uses Varla-embellished barding. Such wolves possess a sure-footedness that lends them stealth despite their glow.\"—Beredalmo the Signifier',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A hint of playfulness. A touch of joy. An aura of mystery. These mix under Jode`s light and take the form of a masked fox who seeks out these traits in their next rider. Or so the priests say. But maybe they`ve had too much moon-sugar.\"—Sulema',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"This wolf might seem a playful Jester`s Festival creature—a performer`s beast ready to entertain. But no. Its sharp wit and sharper teeth care not for another`s amusement, favoring its own. Only its rider is safe from its joy-nips.\"—Mother Regrets',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This hound`s attire may suggest that it was once a fun-loving companion; there is nothing playful about it now. This resurrected creature is not for the faint of heart, but it will show loyalty in not setting you ablaze with its fiery muzzle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Born Guardian Wolf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Alchemists in Cey-Tarn Keep fashion mount armor out of specially treated Culanda stones. No alchemist will say exactly what properties the resulting meadowglass has, but scouts riding meadowglass armored wolves have yet to be captured.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Flint-Pelt Fox',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Legend tells of a Breton hunter who freed a Flint-Pelt Fox from a hagraven`s snare. Now these creatures seek out any warrior who calls hagravens \"foe,\" often lingering around areas terrorized by their hated enemies.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Tears of rage and hatred don`t go wasted in Skyrim. These rare droplets fall upon the snow, calling a spirit of bone and rime from Aetherius. Within seconds, a frost-spiked wolf forms, snarling and bridled with grim purpose.\"—Hef, Tale Collector',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally hailing from Bleakrock Isle, these blue-eyed canines love playing in the frosty air and snow of that distant spit of land. In fact, the locals often bring them inside at night just so that they aren`t awoken by their antics in the morning.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'While Nords claim this lightning-limned wolf seeks out Kyne`s champions to serve, the Stonelore Druids believe differently. Only an imbalance in nature would cause such a creature to coalesce. Its purpose? To find a rider who can restore the balance.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Red-Eyes' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As kits, these rambunctious little trouble-making furballs keep this one on her toes. But their predilection for trouble when young works in your favor—their ability to sense harm is nearly magical. Perfect for messenger work!\"—Tesusah, Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Wolf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_all-maker-wolf.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"On a dark and moonless night, raiders stole into the village with plunder in their eyes and violence in their hearts. Their victory was assured, until a lone howl ripped through the icy night air.\" —The All-Maker`s Land, translated',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Don`t muck with another rider`s wolf, unless you`re ready to meet the All-Maker. These are spirit beasts. They come when summoned, but they`re loyal only to their rider. I nearly lost a finger learning that lesson the hard way.\" —Hlokela, Solitude',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Worshipers on pilgrimage in Mara`s name may—rarely—wake to find one of her favored wolf steeds awaiting them. A not-so-gentle nudge from the Divine Mother.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Spook-Antlers' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Legend says a trading caravan was once ambushed on its way to Elden Root. Only one survived. Days later they arrived safely, slung across the back of a majestic white-and-black elk. Perhaps you might make such a friend if you find yourself in need.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Orphan Elk',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The great expanse between the planes of the Aurbis is endless night, the Outer Darkness of the Void. Some few things, blessedly few things, live in this endless nothingness. And they are strange beyond imagining.\"—Azandar al-Cybiades',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cult priests form a compound with Blackwood herbs and bone salvaged from Quagmire and the Pits. The glowing solution guides this elk and its rider to Prince-favored destinations.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chroma-Blue Dwarven Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Not only is this vamidium crafted from an Ebony and Ebon Steel alloy, but it also has the form of a Dwarven Spider, making it a must-have for those who prefer dark clothes and darker lives.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The long-lost Dwemer never spread as far as Elsweyr, but the Baandari Pedlars go everywhere, and will adapt even ancient technology to their uses.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Dwarven Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_all-maker-dwarven-spider.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:						'name' => 'Senche-Raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Largest of all the furstocks, or \"breeds\" of Khajiit, the Senche-raht is fully intelligent, and in combat often serves simultaneously as warrior and mount.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Whispering-Claw Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Queen`s Claw Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A scholar studying Mnemoli the Blue Star as well as a Whispering Claw warrior, this Senche-raht serves Queen Khamira with both brain and brawn. He volunteered to travel with you, lending you speed and steady companionship.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Goutfang Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After spending many years in a Vrin-Thak adeptorium, this powerful Senche-raht decided it was time to work with someone who regularly goes toward danger. She prefers to learn by watching, however.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Cursebound Senche-raht Darkfang',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Cursebound Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dunewalker Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Spotted Duneracer Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Midnight Cantor Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After spending years expelling dro-m`Athra from Nirn, M`aar decided to follow a new path. Now they hope to explore as much of the Mundus as possible before venturing to the Gates of the Crossing.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Umbral Striped Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When this beautiful beast lost their rider while traversing a labyrinth, this banded Senche-raht left to seek mystical help to get back inside. Since their efforts often lead them into peril, Nushaben hopes to find a partner for the long journeys ahead.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ahz-m`Athra',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_all-maker-senche-raht.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Unlike other Senche-rahts, Thryn has accepted many riders in its time, though only a few have lasted beyond one battle. This is due to Thryn`s habit of testing its rider`s mettle with daring maneuvers and wild risks—all in the name of a good story.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sagacious Psijic Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Worm Cultist Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Legend says that Mannimarco himself indoctrinated this Senche-raht to the way of the Anchorite. It`s unknown if Zalzagh knows whether this is true, or if they have any recollection of life before joining the Worm Cult.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ardor`s Devotion Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Why the flowers? Because this one finds them beautiful, that`s why. Charging into battle together does not mean we can`t enjoy their colors. And a battlefield littered with petals is a sight to behold.\"—Mathi-jo',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Mathi-jo' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Lucent Guardian Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Scaleborn Senche-raht',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ride a stick mount that symbolizes your fiery dreams of all-consuming doom. Complete with flaming mane, tail, and eyes, this thrice-cursed novelty horse makes your stick-riding experience one for the books … of burning horror!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A re-animated Skeletal Bear makes a fearsome mount, and is a favorite of northern Tamriel`s necromancers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Wild Hunt Bear is a forest beast that has lost its Y`ffre-given ability to choose between being plant or animal, reverting to the primal chaos of the Dawn Era.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Branch-Britches' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Bear was also one of the ancient Atmoran animal tokens, associated later with the Nord god Tsun, so the Frostbane Bear has historically been one of the most prestigious mounts a tradition-loving Nord could ride.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bear-Lizard Steed',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Roly-Scaly' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Orcish spellwrights rarely call for boons from Daedric realms beyond Malacath`s Ashpit. Even so, the lure of a raging bear wrought from rock-hard ice is difficult to pass up.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"During the long journey from Nenalata to High Rock, beloved mounts became saviors. A song, nearly forgotten, details how a bear named Sunnawend saved Ayleids from a watery grave as they sought to cross a rain-swollen river.\"—Beredalmo the Signifier',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Aer, the Conjurer Magnificent, summoned the first of these Iron Bears in 1E 2150. According to her notes, the lumbering, ursine frame matches the atronach`s temperament perfectly, making the calling-ritual far easier.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"You need more than colorful barding to harness one of these bears—a splash of blood freed by Neb-Crescen and a teardrop from a watcher`s eye might bind one to your cause. Might. Otherwise, stand clear. You won`t survive their hugs.\"—Mother Regrets',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Foolhardy warriors travel into the charred Deadlands forests to face off against the ursine horrors that reside there. Lucky adventurers return to their homelands alive, but forever haunted by the sound of red-hot claws digging into ashen dirt.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Born Guardian Bear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A whole bear? You grew a whole bear? Well? What are you doing with it still? Get out there! Burn a fort to the ground! Make it hit some rocks with its paws! Bask in bear-y devastation!\"—Glooredel, Vinedusk Ranger',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Vicious, the bear was, all a-rumble with menace, despite its chains. `Let us please Lord Vivec with this two-toned creature. Its growls show promise in a world filled with craven whispers.` And so it began.\"—Armiger Tharys`s Journal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Frost-Eyes' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'All-Maker`s Bear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_all-maker-bear.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The bears of Solstheim have a deep and ancient connection to the All-Maker. When the time comes to serve as a mount to the Skaal, or so the stories go, they enter the corral as mild-mannered as a cub.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sai-Sahan`s Revelry Ursine',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Don`t mind old Honeycheeks, here. He`s just snuffling around to see if you have anything tasty on you. Don`t worry, he`s a strict vegetarian! Although he has been known to swallow a bee or two when he gets deep in a honeycomb.\"—Beniah Bear-friend',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wormwrithe Bear-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The guardians of the Writhing Wall were shaped, warped, and even twisted by the power of the souls contained within. We should care for the beasts and folk touched by the wall. What other choice do right-thinking folk have? \"—Captain Meggrid',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Warrior Wave Badger-Bear',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mount_buraniim-ornaug.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The shallows of Buraniim Isle are rife with a unique subspecies of ornaug. Vibrant and playful, these ornaugs have been known to splash in the surf to attract the curiosity of would-be prey. When the unsuspecting meal draws too close, they strike.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Tales of the Warrior charging through the night bring a sense of peace to those gathered on storm-sodden evenings.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Behold the mammoth. Bred among the majestic trees of Malabal Tor. Let its strength endow you with courage and its even-tempered persistence carry you safely. And let its beauty uplift your soul.\"—Overheard at the Baandari Trading Post',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Na-Totambu War Elephant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Forged by the talented hands of Crown-trained armorers. They turn metals cleaved from Hammerfell earth and worked in local forges into durable protection for this well-trained elephant. Better to be on this warbeast than in front of it.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'War-Ender' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Stone-Slake' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Stone-Nest Landloper',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some customs of Solstice`s Stone-Nest tribe date back well beyond Duskfall. The magical processes they used to shape flesh as they do stone is lost to the modern villagers, but lives on in ancient designs.\"—Muzah-Tei, Stone-Nest Scribbles',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"All-praise to Ald! World-Eater! First of Dragons! Let there be fire in this creature`s belly and rage in its visage! Let its fury be felt by those who oppose us! Let Alduin fuel the power of this beast!\"—Dedication Ceremony',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The first time I saw this skeever at my doorstep, I praised Peryite. Then prostrated myself, as this steed warrants. I`d been called into the world from my cave hideaway. Now we share my Prince`s blessings wherever we travel.\"—Plague Elder Anai No-Nose',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When trained from a pup, these hyenas are sought-after battle mounts. Fiercely loyal to their riders, these relentless pursuers possess endless strength and endurance. Two or more together will form a pack and rile each other into a frenzy.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Fever-Eyes' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"All durzog are relentless in the pursuit of prey, but this sub-species is particularly vicious, especially when following a harpy`s scent. Even experienced handlers sometimes struggle to contain their ferocity on the hunt.\" —Elsweyr: A Rider`s Guide',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ash-Tipped Durzog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Look at that tongue! You can thank Spellwright Domavas for these bug-eating beauties, expanding on Magister Varkenel`s work. I hear he first tried to give them feathers, failed, then came up with this gorgeous steed.\"—Cidius Sosia, Necrom Stablemaster',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally seen as a mistake by its creator, vvardvarks grew in popularity, compelling Telvanni magisters to expand its development. This dark-hued mount is perfectly suited to carry riders in funerary processions honoring revered ancient ancestors.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Animal husbandry experts from Hammerfell and Wrothgar came together in a unique Covenant collaboration to create a good-natured pack animal with a hearty constitution and a pleasing aesthetic. The soft-coated, lovable brekka is the result.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A great dark-furred creature, this beast holds its head high as if a queen among the herd. Other brekkas follow in the wake of this confident leader even in the harshest of climates.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chalk-White Brekka',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_indrik_dawnwood-green.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/mounticon_indrik_illustrious-gold.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pure-Snow Indrik',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some find it strange that the Pure-Snow Indrik should exist in Summerset, where winter never comes, but as the Sapiarch of Elemental Arcana points out, \"Frost magic works everywhere.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Frost-Antler' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Born when a sunset`s light tickles Magicka-imbued bird feathers, the Crimson Indrik possesses a flowing gait. Scholars observe that the indrik`s magical nature promotes self-reflection.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'None dare stare Riften`s native ram in the eyes—it sees threats in many things, and only its owner can meet its gaze without needing to brace for an immediate headbutt. In short, would-be Riften Coalhorn Ram thieves are frequently airborne.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After giants claimed the White Fall area as their own, these dark-ombre rams migrated into Skyrim, where Nords trained them to saddle. Although they frequently butt heads, literally, while being broken in, you`ll not find a more loyal mount.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Hunt-Father`s Get' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Happiest when climbing their native Valus Mountains, these sure-footed mounts grudgingly accept both saddle and reins for as long as their rider allows them to keep moving—or provides them with prodigious amounts of mountain flower treats.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Master-Wizard`s Ram',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Unlike their mainland cousins, the quasigriffs of the Systres Archipelago have vibrant, sea-tinted feathers. Admittedly, Irastimil Direnni never intended to create such colorful creatures. Noble Bretons adore them and travel about High Isle on their backs.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Storm-Eye' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The bird-beast serves Tava in all things. Stand with it in battle and add its strength to your song. By talon and beak, at dawn and dusk, it cries in harmony with its singer.\"—An inscription found near the Battle of Six Hands',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As stablehands across Tamriel can attest, the ravager comes by its name honestly, destroying anything that moves between it and its master. Scholars speculate that the blue Hist of Dead-Water Village brought forth this green-hided breed.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sul-Xan Fleshripper',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Through an Argonian ritual imbued by the Razor Prince`s chaos, this former welwa mount seethes with both fury and destruction in conflagration-touched form. Only the strong-willed can control this beast. Perhaps that`s you?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Seethes-With-Fury' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This savage welwa so interested members of the College of Sapiarchs that they brought several to Sil-Var-Woad for study. To help endear them to the public, an enterprising conservator trained them to saddle and \"lent\" them out into the wild.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Using knowledge gained from the forbidden book Occaecium Beluaria, followers of Hermaeus Mora transformed a welwa into a multi-hued, darkly shimmering steed. He allows his most experienced agents in Tamriel to use them for overland tasks.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Neeti-Nassa' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Grudge-Rock Welwa',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These petulant welwas hail from Wrothgar and more than live up to their name. Hardened by their difficult landscape, the creatures delight in punishing their riders for the smallest slight, whether it`s a late feeding or a slightly too-tight saddle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even the most well-traveled adventurer should tread with care when entering Fargrave. This haunting welwa has an uncanny sense of direction that allows it to traverse the many planes of Oblivion with ease.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Druid-Bound Ursauk',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Tales say Grahtwood`s ancient oaks called these black-furred ursauks from the deep woods. But why? Every reason this one hears is different! Guards for a sapling grove. Help with a werewolf problem. Or maybe for bear hugs.\"—Zhiraz, Traveling Farmhand',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Gallivant across any terrain, seeking your next treasure, with this massive, gilded ursauk. Not only does it bear the blessing of Sai, or so its breeders claim, but its gear contains one element from another successful treasure-seeker`s hoard.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A mix of Skingrad wine, some ashy remnants of Quagmire dreams, and ooze from a Pits-born plague hopper make for a heady solution. After imbibing, neither rider or steed can waver from goals set by the Nightmare Queen and the Master of Tasks.',
esoCollectibleData.php:						'name' => 'Non-Combat Pets',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A foul-smelling Daedric minion, who will follow you loyally, though it won`t fight for you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This gibbering, foul-smelling Daedric minion will follow you loyally, though it won`t fight for you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Skeletal Senche-Leopard^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Is Necromancy always wrong? Not even death can stop this loyal senche-leopard from stalking to adventure at your side!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_191_yaghradarkblue-yellow.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Scamp',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Mind-Shriven Scamp is an unusual specimen. Generally you find them among other mind-shriven creatures, but some addled folk have started including them in their entourage. Peculiar, at best.\"—Warlock Aldaale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Slate-Skinned Daedrat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The cold blue glowing eyes and markings of the Slate-Skinned Daedrat stem from their diet: corpses touched by Molag Bal. Those brave enough to research or even thwart the Lord of Brutality often study these creatures for insight.\"—Phrastus of Elinhir',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dawnstar Dovah-Fly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sea Sapphire Dovah-Fly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Often accompanying ships as they leave port, each blue-purple iridescent Dovah-Fly chooses a person to follow. Each night, the whirr of its gently flitting wings pull its chosen one to slumber, and at sunrise it lightly lands on its \"pet\" to wake them up.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Regal Dovah-Fly^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Many a Vvardenfell youngster growing up in the swamps of West Gash or the Bitter Coast remembers spending happy hours playing \"dodge-dovah\" with these hovering bug-buddies! If hand-raised from larval form, they can become devoted companion animals.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The reddish, or \"Rosy\" Netches are native to the foyadas of the Molag Amur region of Vvardenfell, where they live in a semi-wild state subject to the occasional round-ups of the Netchimen. The calves, sulfurous odor aside, are quite adorable.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Scholars think the iridescent blue Turquoise Nixad must have inherent magical properties, because those wings certainly aren`t big enough to enable it to fly. Yet fly it does, flitting about like a beautiful human-shaped hummingbird moth.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Ancestor Moths that accompany some mystically-attuned mortals are more than mere insects—they are animated by the loving spirits of the dearly departed, and may grant wisdom and awareness to those they visit.\" —Sister Terran Arminus',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Seht`s Dovah-Fly^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Scintillant Dovah-Fly^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Dovah-Fly is a common sight in the oil-slick ravines of the Clockwork City. While its ornate clockworks are a wonder to behold, it`s hard to shake the feeling that it`s always watching you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'There is some debate among naturalists as to whether the Ice Nixad is a separate breed that is mainly seen in the winter because it hibernates during the warm months, or whether it`s just a winter phase of ordinary Nixads that sometimes stays year-round.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Plum Swamp Jelly is the rarest of the so-called \"Flavor\" Jellies, and seeing one is considered by many Argonians to be a sign of good fortune. It`s not at all unusual for an Argonian to wear a Plum Jelly`s feeler as a \"Good Luck Tentacle.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Witches Festival, which celebrates horror and death, also has a regrettable tradition of wanton vandalism associated with it, especially among Tamriel`s callow youth. The so-called \"Hollowjack Netch\" appears to be a victim of this practice.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Gah! Netches! Mine kept getting stuck behind closed doors. So my friend and I made this ghostly netch. Yours for a song, five-claw! Not at all necromantic. Promise!\"—Lanjo, merchant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Long-Winged Bat^F',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Some keep so-called Pocket Watchers as pets, playing off the name of those Pocket Mammoths seen in Wrothgar. Even at their smaller size? Still not the wisest move. Small Daedra are still Daedra, after all, and thus beyond our ken. \"—Warlock Aldaale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Khajiit claim these torchbugs are the light of Jode given form, which allows them to dance amid the moon-sugar cane and bless the crops. Now you can have one flitting about you! After all, having Jode`s blessing is never a bad thing, right?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The night before Waking Day, Iliac Bay Bretons share stories about the Terrible Torchbug of Molag Bal. While the story varies, all agree on one thing: those followed by a cobalt-hued torchbug possess a savagery in battle that haunts any who survive.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some believe that gaining Meridia`s favor is like gripping a double-edged blade tightly with bare hands. Yet, if you perform an action she likes, she may gift you with a White Torchbug—perhaps the least worrisome of her favors!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_pinktorchbug-copy.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"When a Bright Moons Lunar Moth follows you, the blessings of Jone and Jode flutter close behind.\"—Moon-Priest Tedaza',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Pure white, these bats, making them hard to see in wintry conditions. But give one a bit of banana, and it`ll stick close to you for a while. With a constant diet of bananas and other fruits? You are its boon companion.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Normally you don`t see these black bats because they prefer caves and other areas avoided by people. However, if trained, these fellows consider you a member of their colony and hate to leave your side.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"People blessed by these brown bat companions experience very few issues with insects. They love hiding in your pack during the day, and they`ll keep you bug-free while you sleep at night.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Sometimes called Friends of the Caravan, these black-and-white bats migrate among cacti stands in arid regions. Trackers follow their guano to find hydrating, safe cacti when in need. Easily trained to be a companion.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"So colorful! And common around orchards, farms, and other places with cultivated fruit and flowers. A priceless companion for foragers and travelers since they can lead you to food.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Delicate in both form and color, this pink-hued butterfly flits around Elsweyr, Skyrim, Rivenspire—and around you! Tailor Medresi Grulathil looked to her own butterfly companion for inspiration while crafting ceremonial garb honoring Mara in Solitude.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Quiet, tree-shaded lakes attract these blue-purple moths. Legends claim they glide on starlight and rest upon the Moons` reflections in the water. If one follows you away, good luck is said to bless your path.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"After much knowledge-seeking, I learned to summon an illusion of a small, fiery Dragon to follow me. While it`s not the same as the real thing, that endears me to it more. Who wants a real Dragon around, after all?\"—Ninaleon Sightbinder the First',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Known for its brilliant yellow hues, this moth flits through the deciduous fall forests of Cyrodiil almost unseen. Each year, some fly beyond the Heartland`s borders in all directions, as if trying to escape the war-torn province.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Glimmergreen Dovah-Fly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Respect the dovah-fly. They are the spirits of the ancestors given new life. They brighten the quiet tranquility of ponds and streams. What better afterlife is there?\"—Druid Henneque Blakeley',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Yoltoor Dovah-Fly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Shimmering like fire, these dovah-flies dart around port cities, eating many of the nuisance insects that pester transported livestock. Recently, merchants started training and selling them to help others with insect issues.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Don`t let those icy blue eyes fool you. It`s their claws you need to keep an eye on—they can shatter stone, leaving behind nothing but glowing rubble. Thankfully, they`re actually quite good-natured creatures once they imprint on you.\"—Divayth Fyr',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Guardian Flit-Flit' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These brown-furred bats pollinate flowers along the Xylo River. Without them, nature`s web in the Valenwood would be deeply disrupted. Plus they look adorable when they sneeze.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Druids say the moths are ash made manifest. They leap from the flames of Mount Firesong and flutter away on the breeze. Nonsense! I`ve seen a moth ignite and then emerge from the coals like a cocoon.\"—Feather-Brained Teeska',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_bright-moons-dragon-imp.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This impressive vision is the work of a very dedicated illusion imp. The shimmering form sparks the adoration of all who see it, making for easy handouts and safe havens for this tiny so-called Dragon.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mead-Dancer Honeybee',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Bees are simple, really. They respect power. That`s why they follow a queen. Just act like you`re supposed to be in charge and they`ll work for you. Show any weakness, any hesitation? That`s when you get stung.\"—Hei Honey-Hands',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Like the Warrior-Poet himself, this striking butterfly is bisected by two distinct color palettes. The Tribunal`s faithful consider it a good omen to see one of these creatures, and a blessing from Lord Vivec himself if one chooses to follow you.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Golden Wisp',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Celebrate the 10-Year Anniversary by dancing in the golden light of this summoned wisp.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Solstice Flats Dovah-Fly',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Isolation from the rest of Tamriel for generations has caused the local dovah-fly population to develop bright, unusual colors. They seem to be a warning to predators, although the Solstice dovah-fly itself isn`t poisonous.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Olank-Ja' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Rimmen gossips speculate this imp takes the shape of a miniature green Dragon in praise to Peryite, who helped the little beasts escape flu-ridden Orcrest.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Sail the waters of the Azurian Sea long enough and you`re bound to see the migration of the water-moths. That`s where I got this fellow. It had a weak wing and landed on my ship, so I took care of it. Now, it refuses to leave me.\"—Navigator Stacia',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A loyal steam-powered Dwarven Spider, fueled by magicka from a soul gem that will last for eras.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A perky crab buddy whose rust-colored shell covers a cheerful, inquisitive demeanor.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A Dwarven Sphere of the long-lost Dwemer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some scholars believe Argonians are descended—or were uplifted—from these tree-dwelling swamp lizards. True or not, they make great pets, affectionate and low-maintenance.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Striped Senche-Panther',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This elegant senche-panther is a distant relative of the Khajiit, though it cannot speak like the cat-folk.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Deep-Moss Ash Hopper^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Deep-Moss Ash Hopper is native to southern Vvardenfell, where it`s most commonly found in the fungal-forested uplands and the coastal marshes. They`ve been adopted as mascot bugs by the Buoyant Armigers, who admire their green carapaces.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Blue-Cap Shroom Shalk^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Gold-Cap Shroom Shalk^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It isn`t well known outside financial circles, but somewhere in the basement or sub-level of every bank in Morrowind you`ll find the institution`s mascot, a sweet old waddling Gold-Cap Shroom Shalk. The symbolism, of course, is obvious.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Red Pit Wolves of southern Skyrim are known for their aggression and ferocity, and you can see that even in their puppies, adorable as they are. They love to play, but that means play-fighting, so expect to get chewed on as you tussle!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bal Foyen Nix-Hound',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Who says a giant, aggressive, blood-sucking insect can`t make a loveable pet? Not the Dark Elves of Bal Foyen, who breed them as trackers, watch-hounds, and netch-deflators.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Full-grown echateres may be stubborn and ornery, but the baby Echalettes are playful and, frankly, just plain adorable. Once a young Echalette bonds with its master, it becomes a devoted companion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Your new best friend is a giant blood-sucking insect bloated with pustulant, lethal contagion! It`s bursting with both infection and affection—for you!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Roly-Poly' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Moonlight Senche-Tiger',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Moonlight Senche-Tigers have been the sleek and silvery guardians of the Khajiiti temples of the moons ever since the revelation of the Riddle`Thar.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The common or Kindlespit Dragon Frog is an engagingly preposterous little pal whose antics never fail to amuse. Hammerfell tales say the huge Dragons of ancient legend were all turned into these tiny flame-puffing hoppers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The slug-like Sloads of Thras bred the flame-hued Tangerine Dragon Frog so they could be spotted more easily in their archipelago`s murky lagoons. Some say they were bred to be pets, but the Sload word for them translates as \"snacks.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The comical Blue Oasis Dragon Frog is native to Hew`s Bane, and before they were bred as pets could be found only on that Hammerfell peninsula. These little bug-eaters are popular mascots at open-air taverns.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Lion Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'If you domesticate a Senche-Lion Cub when it`s young enough, it will follow you everywhere, no matter how dangerous. And your enemies will burn from the cuteness.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'How did this one become a so-handsome copperback Badger? M`aiq will tell you. One day near Balmora he met two Telvanni wizards, one of whom said, \"Everything I tell you is true,\" while the other said, \"Everything I tell you is a lie….\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Clouded Senche-Leopard Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Of all the varieties of wild senche-cats, the Clouded Leopard may be the most beautiful. Their cubs love to play-fight, and stalk tiny bugs with the most hilariously serious expressions.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though it may some day grow into a horrific face-eating behemoth, when it`s young the Haj Mota Hatchling is undeniably cute. For a while, they are trainable, come when called, and happily waddle after their masters wherever they may go.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Khajiit of Corinthe believe the all-black Dark Moons Lynx is the worldly incarnation of Southpaw, the feline companion to Rajhin the Footpad, god of thieves. It`s said Southpaw keeps watch while Rajhin is breaking and entering.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dozen-Banded Vvardvark^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The blue-scaled Cobalt Sep Adder is the rarest of the wild varieties, and almost never seen in captivity. They are particularly prized by the royalty of Hammerfell`s contentious city-states, as they`re said to be able to detect poison in drinks and food.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Black-Ears' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Tiger Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s a striped Senche-Tiger Cub. What more could you need to know? \"Ah,\" you ask, \"but is it magical?\" Just look in those eyes for your answer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Senche-Panther Kitten',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Rajhin the Purring Liar had so many shadows that some of them took on lives of their own, becoming black senche-panthers who stalk freely through Elsweyr—just like this kitten that plays with my tail.\" —Clan Mother Ahnissi',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dro-m`Athra Senche Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Combine Adorable with Abominable, and what do you get? The dro-m`Athra Senche Cub, the cutest thing ever to come out of the Dark Behind the World. Dance, kitten, dance!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Leopard Cub^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The senche-leopard is one of the most feared predators of the Tenmar Forest in central Elsweyr, but if one of its adorable cubs can be adopted when young, it makes a fiercely loyal companion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Striped Senche-Panther Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Striped senche-panthers are popular mascots of the Baandari Pedlars of Elsweyr. Incredibly adorable as cubs, even when small they can be trained like magpies to fetch shiny things back to their masters.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This bluish breed of Vvardenfell aerial reptile, known as the Azure or Ascadian Cliff Strider, is prized by flying-lizard fanciers as the prettiest and most ornamental of its species. Bonus: its screech terrifies crying babies into silence.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Strides-So-High' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Credit for the irresponsible and foolhardy project of domesticating the Craglorn Welwa is usually claimed by the Iron Orcs, who are always looking for ways to prove that they`re \"more bad-tusk\" than the Orcs of Wrothgar or Skyrim.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Ears gro-Loth`Na' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Shadowghost Senche-Panther^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In Elsweyr, being seen in the company of an uncanny Shadowghost Senche-Panther will put one under suspicion of being a Namiira cultist—or even a disguised dro-m`Athra.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Flame Atronach Senche-Jaguar^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The first summoner of this fiery kitten was attempting to compel the Daedra into the form of a full-grown senche-jaguar. Though initially embarrassed by her mistake, she nonetheless grew an attachment to this far more adorable form.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Though smaller than its mount counterpart,\" wrote arch-conjurer Corvus Direnni, \"it`s necessary to take all precautions when handling the Flame Atronach Pack Wolf. I`ve found their curiosity insatiable, especially when near flammable objects.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These perky metal creations are known to pack quite the pinch. Though their rust-resistant coatings do enable them to enter into water, they`re far better at sinking than swimming.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Spotted Snow Senche-Leopard^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even for the elusive senche-leopard, the Spotted Snow is a rare variety. Despite its frosty-looking fur, this adorable companion makes for a great cuddle buddy during long winter nights.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Since our Incarnatoriums can be modified to produce Fabricants modeled on almost any creature of Tamriel Above, why are Scorpion Fabricants of differing sizes so popular? They`re our most-requested fabs!\" says Clockwork Apostle Dringest.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These mysterious green-glowing Brassilisks have been showing up in the environment outside the Brass Fortress. Some Clockwork Apostles suspect there`s a rogue Incarnatorium assembling them somewhere out in the Radius.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Steam-Driven Brassilisk^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Karth Winter Hound is the snow-white breed of the Markarth Bear Dog, snowy year-round for hunting in Skyrim`s snow-capped peaks. Some Reach clans reserve the Winter Hounds solely for chieftains.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Like the Purple Daggerback, the breed of Flameback Boars clearly had some kind of brush with the uncanny that imbued them with magical aspects. Regular boars just don`t have crimson glowing eyes and flame-colored bristle crests down their backs.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Despite the fact that this night-black senche-tiger cub has burning paws and flaming eyes, it`s so adorable it might be a nightmare you never want to awaken from!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In \"The Tail of Ysgramor`s Cat,\" the Harbinger`s Sabre Cat hunting companion is described as being festooned with Atmoran Frostbane talismans, and some tradition-loving modern Nords still decorate their Sabre Cats in the same manner.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Totem-Tusk' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'To accustom their Frostbane Wolves to the click-clacking of dangling talismans and totems, the ancient Nords began dressing their companion wolves in Frostbane garb from an early age.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The hardy ponies of the frozen north look even shaggier when they`re decorated with Frostbane hair-knots and ancient Nord totems. Whether the talismans keep the cold away is impossible to tell, but it`s certain these ponies never lose their good cheer.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Sweet young things like to give this one kittens as keepsakes,\" says Eye of the Queen Razum-dar, \"but raising a pet is not consistent with Raz`s romantic but itinerant life of intrigue. Perhaps you could give cute Ja`khajiit a good home, yes?\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Prong-Eared Grimalkin^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Prong-Eared Grimalkins are widely regarded as having supernatural powers thanks to their ability to appear almost instantly when a container of cat food is opened, and to fit themselves into boxes that seem entirely too small for them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Native to Summerset Isle, the gaudy Coral Mudcrab has elaborate coral growths on its back, as well as a claw that looks comically over-sized, but which is surprisingly functional. Count fingers after petting.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_192_indrik-springtide-green.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Fell-Chaser' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_193_indrik-illustrious-gold.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When spring comes to the sun-dappled forests of southern Wrothgar, Echatere babies are sometimes born with temporary spotted camouflage that fades as the Echalette matures. It`s pretty while it lasts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This perky but enigmatic equine glows with Magicka through the mystic runes that embellish its possibly-illusory epidermis. Enchanting!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The thief-god Rajhin is said to have stolen these enchanted purple Ponies from somewhere in Oblivion, but when his worshipers are asked where he got them, they just laugh and say, \"Noweyr!\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Neigh-Neigh' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When a cub, the young Atmoran Snow Bear is a lap-clambering cuddle bug, a friendly fuzzball whose demeanor is completely at odds with the fierce reputation of adult Snow Bears. Enjoy them while they`re still small!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_200_dwarven-ebonyyellow.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Teal-Faced Fellrunner^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_194_teal-fellrunner.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Craglorn Companions of Belkarth had no luck at all exporting Fellrunners for the High Rock and Hammerfell pet markets—until they sold a flock of the Teal-Faced variety to Fahara`jad`s menagerie in Sentinel. Suddenly they were all the rage!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Gryphons that nest on the highest pinnacles of Eton Nir, the tallest mountain on Summerset, have a distinctive bluish tint to their plumage. Some sapiarchs call this sky-blue camouflage, but the Priests of Auri-El see in it a touch of the Divine.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Be scared—be very scared!\" say this pup`s big fiery eyes. \"Please?\" But no matter how much it tries to frighten like a grown-up Nightmare Wolf, this flaming fuzzball is still completely adorable.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_195_seaadder-yellow.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Noble Riverhold Senche-Lion Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Even as cubs, the litter-mates of the noble Riverhold senche-lion prides exhibit the breed`s hallmark attributes of courage and loyalty, bravely defending their masters against encroaching beetles and butterflies!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Pride-Cub' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_196_giantspider-goldenback.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pale-Plume Fledgling Gryphon^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Less common than the usual variety, the Pale-Plume Gryphons are found only along the seacoast cliffs near the Tower of Dusk in southeast Summerset. Their Fledglings make engaging pets that can be trained to follow their masters even into danger.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Touch-Me-Not' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Bug-Biter' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Prong-Eared Odd-Eyed Cat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_prongearoddeyed-cat.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Cats with odd-colored eyes see into the depths of those around them. Those with white fur? They see into time itself.\" —Zamarak',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This smaller breed of haj mota lurks in the brackish estuaries of Black Marsh`s southern coast, camouflaged by the gray color of the murky tidewater. When hand-raised from hatching, they make surprisingly pleasant pets.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A haj mota is an ambush predator, waiting patiently in concealment until its prey should come into attack range. The Verdigris breed tends to hide in algae-covered pools where its color acts as camouflage.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Bear-Lizard Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though the adult Bear-Lizards can be quite intimidating, even fearsome, the roly-poly lizard cubs are disarmingly cute. (For reptiles, that is.)',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Scaly-Boo' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pony-Lizard',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When young Argonian egg-siblings tell their creche-parents they want a pony, this is what they mean. And now that you`ve seen it, don`t you want one, too?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Lizard Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'True, it does hiss rather than meow, and has shiny scales rather than soft fur, but otherwise the Senche-Lizard Cub is just as adorable as any other kitten.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wolf-Lizard Pup',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Wolf-Lizard Pup is simply adorable when it tries to howl, just hisses instead, and looks ever so confused.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Guar-Lizard Calf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though you know it`s just going to grow up and become big, dumb, scaly livestock, how can you resist those lizard-calf eyes?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Most Echalettes are docile and fawn-like, but not the Badger Ruff breed, which are strangely fierce and irritable. They`re so ornery they`ve been known to chase away inquisitive Sabre Cats.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Jerboas, you say? Ah, yes, the little jumping skeevers with the so-big ears. There are many in the Ashen Scar, and if you catch one when it`s small, it makes for a pleasant, fuzzy friend. I had one when I was a kitten!\" —Shuzirri of Riverhold',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hot-Blooded Bantam Guar',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When asked about the rumor that the Hot-Blooded Bantam Guar had been bred as a vampiric sub-species by the disgraced mage Darvasen before he was exiled from Shad Astula, Arch-Mage Valeyn replied, \"What nonsense! They just like to eat tomatoes. Trust me.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Gory-Guar' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A fur-less, cold-blooded reptile with icy blue eyes that comes from the frozen, far-north, and in-all-likelihood legendary continent of Atmora? Bah. I refuse to believe it.\" —Phrastus of Elinhir',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Snow-on-Scales' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Arena Lions are trained to absolute obedience, whether as sturdy and savage Craglorn companions or as pit-fighting beasts taught to drag out a kill for the entertainment of an audience.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pedlar Pack Senche-Lion Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'To prepare their Senche-Lion mounts, the Baandari Pedlars train them with full gear as cubs. Despite the tack, these cubs pounce and play as kittens do.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Need some happiness in your day? The Alabaster Jerboa is your answer. Its hopping and air-dancing acrobatics can bring a smile to even the grumpiest Dark Elf.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Sunspire Ice-Fire Senche-Cub',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Before ice-fire senche-lions become mounts, they start as adorable cubs. But be careful! These cute creatures still require careful handling due to their mix of cold and flame.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senche-Serval Kitten',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_senche-serval-kitten.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"While carrying out an assignment from Larnatille in my role as Sub-Sapiarch of Domestic Livestock, I created a mount both loyal and majestic. Though the kitten stage is … a bit trying.\" —Corderil of Sunhold',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The reason behind the creation of this tabby was simple: Cats kill rodents. Mummified and mobile cats will kill rodents indefinitely. Thus this bandage-bound pet was … born?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Do not ask me how this creature came to be. Or not be. It just is. But, perhaps do not kill chickens in already-haunted places.\"—Geem-Sai, Butcher',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Cock-a-doodle-Boo' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This cub from the Cult of the New Moon will happily trundle along behind you as long as you keep it well-fed.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dread-Aurelian Dragonslayer Wolf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ebon-Glow Indrik^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though many associate darkness with evil, those looking at the Ebon-Glow Indrik come to understand that darkness is simply the absence of light—neither good nor bad in itself. A soothing thought that calms fears, much like this magical indrik does.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Frost-Light Indrik^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Jade-Crown Dragonslayer Wolf^F',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'You needn`t know Conjuration magic to have an atronach companion—Clan Direnni mages have gifted bear cubs of that provenance to those they deem worthy. They can be oddly heart-warming despite their frosty form.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"A mage from Lilmoth found a way to, ahem, `tame` these green slimes. Yes, it will follow you around, leaving a disgusting trail of slime, but it`s hardly docile. My apprentice`s so-called `pet` woke me by trying to engulf my face.\"—Aleri Andalor',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Though the arcane markings on this gray pocket mammoth indicate its status as a sacrificial offering, these creatures often end up trundling along after soft-hearted souls like yourself.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'After news of the Seventh Legion`s presence near Hallin`s Stand spread, several Evermore citizens moved quickly to protect some at-risk fauna, among them a breed of easily domesticated jackals. Now one of these fierce companions can roam at your side.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Integrating research left behind by Ahzidal the Enchanter, I crafted a bear cub from spores acquired from a well-traveled merchant. This creature bumbles around a bit more than its animal counterpart, but it glows! Perfection!\"—Mage Naleldil',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"To the surprise of none but the most hard-hearted, I made a tumbling ball of fungal-fur in the form of a senche cub. How could I not? And shame on any who pass this adorable bundle of spores without smiling.\"—Mage Naleldil',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Challenged by a colleague, I created a pony-fungus creature. The first few stood as still as statues, so I added manic morels from Dementia. That livened things up considerably. If you adopt one, I suggest keeping it out of your parlor.\"—Mage Naleldil',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The sound of wind gusting through dusklit, ice-laden trees heralds a Rimedust Indrik`s birth. These indriks emanate a sense of deep calm wherever they go.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Coldspring Nix-Hound',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Dark Elves of House Hlaalu, knowing that Vvardenfell isn`t the only place with deadly flora, fauna, and folk, bred a nix-hound that can thrive in different environments. Even with its gorgeous blue-purple shading, it still possesses a menacing air.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ice-Glow Salamander',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'While studying arcane husbandry, Mage Naleldil discovered a long-forgotten Ayleid ritual capable of granting luminescent qualities to common salamanders. Now, due to an unexpected population explosion, she gives them to those who impress her.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Some Alinor scholars claim these indriks form when Magicka mingles with the petals of early-blooming roses. Others note that the roses` thorns need to have drawn blood first. Regardless, this creature inspires creativity in any it follows.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'As trees awaken in the spring, the first light of dawn sparks the formation of a Sapling Indrik from Magicka-touched acorns. Boundless hope fills those they choose to follow.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Skald-Muse Fledgling Gryphon',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Decades ago, Nords whispered stories of a reclusive dark-furred lynx that ate spirits barred from Sovngarde. Imagine the Nords` surprise when they found these lynxes domesticated as tent guards during a raid on Reach natives.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Its amber-gold glimmer creates a warmth that one stablemaster states, \"Can get you through chilly nights under the Skyrim stars.\" All it takes to keep one of these vale fawns at your side is a lick of honey now and again.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'One scholar studying vale fawns notes that the purple-hued Orchidfall fawn—named after a now-lost flora-filled cavern in Skyrim—enjoys eating flowers. \"Give it a flower, and it`s your friend for life!\" Do you have your flower in hand?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Energetic Dwarven Shock-Spider',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Barnacle-Back Coral Crab',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'While many crustaceans struggle to remove clinging barnacles, the Barnacle-Back Coral Crabs appreciate the company. Some naturalists believe the crabs welcome their guests` sharpened shells as an added protective layer. But maybe they`re just gregarious!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Talking with the trainers of the wolf riders that Versidue-Shaie established in 2E 4 allowed me to see the armored pups at play. I adored how they bonelessly stretched on the ground. Hard to believe they grow to be so fierce!\"—Mirannah of Gwylim',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"In 2E 5, companies using the new enchanted barding designed by Versidue-Shaie`s battlemages received their orders: hunt and kill Reman loyalists. Though initially only horses, ponies and more earned the special barding and training.\"—Mirannah of Gwylim',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Potentate first mounted up on guar steeds in 2E 27 under the Red Mountain`s shadow, but they trained guar calves to the saddle just outside Mournhold. One barded calf demanded nose-pats from me when I visited—I couldn`t resist.\"—Mirannah of Gwylim',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This fastidious little jerboa originated from Orcrest, but recent events saw them scurry away or go into deep hiding among the nooks and crannies of that ill-fated city. With coaxing, one of these delightful little creatures might venture forth with you!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Jewel-Feathered Sep Adder',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Dreams-of-Flight' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Striking scarlet hues mark this ancestor lizard, which some claim are the ancestors of the Bright-Throats. While this hospitality-minded tribe remains silent on this claim, these lizards are known to comfort the pain of others by nuzzling them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This boar`s regal bearing and attire indicate a level of breeding that would not allow for \"cute\" or \"comical\" behavior. Nothing could be further from the truth! He digs for his own truffles, plus rumors indicate he loves batter-based treats.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Those traversing the Niben River can see these fellrunners racing along the banks, avoiding dangers while seeking safe water. Enterprising merchants capture and sell them to buyers captivated by their teal-feathered, avian beauty.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Taming even a young terror bird requires patience, full-coverage armor, and even more patience. The result, however, can put pause to any seeking to cast you in the role of victim. Plus these fledglings cuddle so nicely while making cute sleeping noises!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These cerulean-toned haj mota hatchlings learn to fend for themselves amid ice caves, frozen wastes, and crevasses early on. If you tame one, not only do you have a future terror loyal to you, but you also gain its keen survival instinct in frosty lands.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Visiting the Stitches requires a certain amount of fortitude and bravado. Living there, as do these cavies, involves hiding and good timing, as well. Gain a cavy`s hard-won trust, and you gain a furry friend seeking neck-snuggles for life.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In the wild, Topaz Terror Birds cloak themselves in wind-blown sand to ambush unsuspecting prey. This little fledgling is keen to practice the technique, so be sure to warn your companions before a sandstorm hits. No one wants to lose a toe!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'According to the Ash`abah, if you receive one of these fierce sep adders as a gift and you both survive for a year with each other, you have passed the first trial necessary to trade in poisons. Bonus? You keep the jewel-toned creature—if you live.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Bite-Bite' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Said to have been bred by Coral-Splitter Goblins to hunt for fresh fish, these aqua-blue and coral-striped durzogs spread to the shores of Topal Bay decades ago. To this day, they still love to dive into the surf and snag aquatic bounty!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mzark Jade-Cap Shroom Shalk',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Wardens of Morthal ride large, hulking Sunback Bears into battle. While the full-sized bears tend to scare villagers, cubs are more easily accepted. Plus, the cubs` tiny ears can get the staunchest of merchants to lower their prices.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Cat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The Mind-Shriven usually have no concept of the self, but this feline appears to be as content with its nature as always. It seems that Molag Bal himself cannot enslave a cat.\"—Warlock Aldaale',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ironclad Senche-Serval Kitten',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Contrary to popular belief, this cute-yet-terrifying Evergloam creature does not eat shadows to grow larger. But they definitely do win at games that involve hiding in murky places—a gift from Nocturnal herself, perhaps?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Cey-Tarn Keep dog-handlers made armor training wolf pups a priority after older members of the pack gnawed their plate-harnesses to pieces. The practice lives on in this pup who proudly displays his Elven panoply as he trots beside his owner.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The distinctive blue colors of the Iliac Bay Crab make it both a sought-after adventuring friend for those who adore crabs as companions and a target for fisherfolk seeking the shellfish`s tender meat. Are you the former, the latter, or maybe both?',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Hay-Crown Chub Loon',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hay-Crown Chub Loons were revered as omens of good harvests until one winter in Rivenspire, when desperate farmers discovered that these creatures were delectable. Druids took the dim-witted, delicious birds with them when they fled to High Isle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Deek-beeko' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Flirts-With-Tail' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Spring blossoms nod their heads as if recognizing kin in this Elf-pampered companion. Some caretakers claim these gryphons provide a sense of ease to those who care for them—and pain for those who seek their demise.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Before the druids, before the coin-barons, before even the noble houses, the hermit crab held dominion over the Systres. Hauling its belongings wherever it travels, its beady eyes give you a look that seems to say, \"We`re not so different, you and I.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Where`d I get the cat? Cards. Poor thing was used in place of coin by some pet-smuggling lowlife. I`m teaching her how to count cards and fetch me a pint.\"—Privateer Mahk',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The eye-catching tail pouf of the ringtail jerboa makes for a daring fashion statement especially appreciated by the aristocracy of High Isle. It`s also, of course, used for balance.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"See the crab`s big tidepool eyes? Delicious. Their big claws that can fell saplings with one snip? The meat inside is as juicy as the fruit about to drop off a tree. Trust me. Keep one of these around in case you need a snack.\"—Xoko, Hee-Tepsleel Chef',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Once bred for their ability to smell when a grape is perfectly ripe, the Sweetgrape Dragon Frog is now considered an invasive pest. Winemakers go to great lengths to keep the grape-loving frog away from their vineyards.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silver-Bellied Guarling',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Telvanni magisters use only the hardiest of the fire-hued fungi when magically coercing it into a new form. Whether one such magister crafted these pleasantly companionable spore ponies causes snippy disagreements among mages and scholars alike.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The ancestry of this rambunctious dark-furred pup goes all the way back to the Five Hundred Companions of Ysgramor. That doesn`t stop it from acting like a mischievous little furball, though!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"To fear change wastes time one could spend engaging with the moment. These dark creatures are gifts from our past to both voh-vastei and those who need to be led into the present.\"—Nisswo Uaxal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Chip-Chip' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Zuugarz of Orsinium says she first discovered these obsidian-worked animunculi, a claim backed up by the loyal construct that follows her around. She`s since learned her scholarly companion \"gifted\" it to her, but that`s not something she`s eager to share.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Nightmares of scorpions. So many colors, but the dream-sea blue one tipped with angry-eyes red stepped forth. I woke to see this wondrous creature. A gift from Vaermina? My partner says they live in Satakalaam, but how did one get to Wayrest?\"—Gaelle',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Angry-Dreams' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Rumors that Systres Fauns call these gray-hued young deer to their frolics stem from the markings both share. Undoubtedly, the grog that accompanies such tales has something to do with these claims. Whatever the case, they`re adorable in the extreme.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Knows-Everything' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Give one of these green-shelled beauties food, and they`ll follow you around a bit. Keep it up, and you`ve a friend for life. If they were smaller, I`d let them dangle from my ears, but they settle into my pack well enough.\"—Aetis Salvitto',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Also called the \"Dog of the Watch,\" these dark-furred mutts work alongside sailors on their docked ships. Recently, the craze among Gonfalon Bay nobles involves sponsoring the care, feeding, and, oddly, hats for these beloved canines.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Graht-Oak Squirrel',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"These large, floof-tailed beasts love to scamper around their home Graht-oak, tucking nuts and seeds into hidey-holes around its roots. Keep an acorn in your pocket, and you`ve a friend for life—or until it sneaks that acorn away from you!\"—Amridil',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Half-Hatched Guarling',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In Telvanni lands, haj mota sometimes lay their eggs in broken catacombs or abandoned cemeteries. The hatchlings acquire a coating of green grave-mold on their shells and become sensitive to the presence of ghosts.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Gray-Tongue' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Clockwork Nix-Hound',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A fabricant from the hidden laboratories of Sotha Sil, the clockwork nix-hound is a small but lifelike imitation. It even \"hunts\" and consumes tiny scraps of metal in its vicinity. Watch out for your coinpurse!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Much like the pocket mammoths first domesticated near Bonerock Cavern, these creatures are docile and affectionate, plus make excellent livestock. This sub-species is particularly prized among breeders for its distinctive fur color.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Star-Orphan Fawn',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_star-orphan-fawn.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Cute little critters, aren`t they? The white pelt helps them blend into the mountains of Skyrim. That`s good, because they`re just about the tastiest thing the winter has to offer. Except for that one. He`s off limits.\"—Narrald Snow-Bourne',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_wenayawend-wolf-pup.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Meridia-Touched Asp',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The eye-catching hue of this haj mota may be beautiful, but it belies a fiery demeanor. Haj motas are known for their harsh temperaments, but this one is not to be trifled with. Thankfully, it`s too small to do more than snap at ankles.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"These mudcrabs developed their shine as both a defensive tactic and mating ritual. By angling their bodies, they can reflect blinding rays at would-be predators or signal their availability to potential mates.\"—Mirrormoor: More Than an Illusion',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Look at the scales on this one! I did not know Useful Lizards could be so beautiful. Perhaps that is its use? Spreading beauty throughout the marsh? I will wallow with it and see if the Hist grant any more insight.\"—Thinks-too-Much, Stormhold',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Scales-that-Shine' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The metamorphic nature of the voriplasm is a bit of a passion of mine. Nothing in all of Tamriel is as adaptive as this simple-minded gel. My lab sample collection grows daily, showing unbelievable specificity in their adaptations.\"—Gabrielle Benele',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Unassuming at a glance, the closer one looks at a mirrorworm, the more mesmerizing they become. The creature`s soft form is protected by glistening reflective scales that also serve to confuse and intimidate would-be predators.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s rumored that these little amphibians may be as long-lived as the Ayleids themselves used to be. Found only in Rivenspire near the Erokii Ruins, they are highly prized for their unique coloration and ability to regrow their own missing limbs.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Sir Clacks-a-lot' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Snowclaw Senche-Serval Kitten',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The shards on this wildcat`s body are dull and safe to touch. The same can`t be said for its fangs and claws, which prick like needles. As it grows in size, those shards become razor-sharp glass—a terrifying defense mechanism.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Mudcrab',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This mudcrab is a frisky little crustacean pal who`s at home in the water or out of it. Gilded and gussied up as a 10-year tribute.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => '10-Year Anniversary Monkey',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This well-dressed monkey is lively and cheerful, even in the grimmest of dungeons. Gilded and gussied up as a 10-Year tribute.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Orsinium Tiger-Lynx',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Mudcrab',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"As I looked into the cold, crustacean`s eyes, it snapped through my net like sword to skin. It was then that I realized that they were the predator, and I was the prey.\"—Bikkus-Xu, Angler',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Root-Whisper Crested Dart Frog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Sniff-Snap' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Many of these hatchlings come from western Murkmire. Raised by the Dead-Water tribe to appear strong and spark fear, some secretly find them cute to keep as pets.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"If your horse spares a red-tailed scorpion from being crushed underfoot, the scorpion was sent by the First Serpent to share your camp. To keep it free from vermin.\"—From Grandee Yaghoub`s writings',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A colorful little friend happy to follow you into even the most disease-ridden dens. Many find the smell off-putting? But this true soul of Peryite goes snout-first into pestilence with a grin.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ash-Tipped Durzog Pup',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Mind-Shriven Reef Viper',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Members of Legion Zero tuck their ophidian friends into a pack in anticipation of their dark blessing. Once they let the snake taste the Blood of Coldharbour, they create an undying mind-shriven companion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Pulsing with heat, this vvardvark is ideal for the Dark Elf scholar who doesn`t mind an occasional burn. Its molten skin allows it to traverse the Ashlands with ease, while its whip-like tongue singes and cooks insects as soon as it catches them.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Chalk-White Brekka Calf',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These furtive bantam guar are particularly skittish. Their mottled coloring helps them blend in with the foliage of Port Telvannis, though their eyes sometimes give them away. They`re experts at avoiding predators and would-be pet owners with ease.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Nip-Yip' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Na-Totambu Pocket Elephant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Nibble-Nibble' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Grant the bird-beast`s young succor in the name of Tava and Diagna. Strengthen it each day so that it may lend its song to yours.\"—An inscription found near the Battle of Six Hands',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Keel-Sakka Crocodile Hatchling',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Tum-Taleel along the Keel-Sakka River occasionally train crocodiles to help them gather tribute from those crossing the river`s bridge. Currently, they have no trained crocodiles due to reasons they prefer not to explain. Their loss, your opportunity!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Gem-Bellied Sep Adder',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A Hammerfell tale says that if you follow one of these gem-bellied creatures from dawn to dusk, it will go to ground near a hidden source of water. Where it vanishes into the earth, dig, and you`ll find enough water for days.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Krona-Konu Danger Frog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A bedtime story on Solstice tells of how the hermit crabs living around Broken Light Temple used to be a brilliant white. When Meridia`s blessing shattered, these creatures also lost their light and have remained midnight-dark ever since.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Superstitious sailors along Abecean trade routes like to keep one caged light-furred rat aboard, claiming it knows when pirates draw near.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This green-eyed feline is a distant relative of the Alfiq Khajiit.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Alik`r Dune-Hound',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Dune-Hound is the loyal dog of the Redguard hunters of the Alik`r.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Abecean Ratter is famed from Hegathe to Woodhearth as a prime rodent-catcher.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Markarth Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Fierce and courageous fighters, the hunters of Western Skyrim use small packs of these dogs to pursue bears. The Bear-Dogs track, corner, and harry the bears until the hunters can arrive with their spears.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Copperback Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Copperback variant of the Markarth Bear-Dog is renowned for its responsiveness to training, but keep an eye on it, or will get into all sorts of mischief. Especially keep an eye on its eyes, which are two different colors!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Originally bred on the Isle of Artaeum, the black-and-white Domino Pig is so smart it can count to five and learn to recognize its name.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Black Mask Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'This variant of the Bear-Dog is a favorite of the Markarth Watch—and of the thieves who attempt to evade them. The Watch uses them to sniff out trouble, while the outlaws employ them to keep an eye out for the Watch!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'White cats are sacred to Dibella, the Lady of Love, and all white cats are said to be her representatives in the animal kingdom. A House of Dibella will typically have three or four milk-white cats within its walls.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'White-Gold Imperial Pony^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The White-Gold Imperial Pony was said to have made its debut as the birthday present for a noble`s daughter, though which family claims this prestige is still hotly debated throughout Cyrodiil.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These short-haired, large-eared cats are a common sight in Mages Guildhalls, where it`s said their keen senses enable them to detect all manner of intruders, even those that are magically concealed or from realms of Oblivion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Orcs of Wrothgar have a hardy breed of goats well-suited to the area`s rugged terrain and changeable climate. Each goatherd particularly prizes his herd`s master Buck Goat; these tend to be both intelligent and pugnacious, good animal companions.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Big-Eared Ginger Mouser^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Ginger Mouser is a favorite barn cat of grain farmers all across central Tamriel, not just because it keeps the storage bins rodent-free, but also for its affectionate personality and goofy good looks.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When the Karth Winter Hound has puppies, it even softens the Briarhearts of the Reachmen. Who`s a good barbarian pup-pup, then? Is it you? It IS you!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Big-Eared Ginger Kitten^n',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Big-Eared Ginger, a favorite shipboard pet, is just about the most playful kitten in Summerset. Its over-sized sound catchers enable it to hear every tiny motion within range before it pounces upon it.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hardy and good-natured, the faithful Skyrim Paint Pony wants to be near its master regardless of the weather, leaning into the wind even in a tundra blizzard.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Pining for a perfect pet? Perhaps you`re a person who`d prefer a pleasantly playful piglet, pearly-white, pretty, and partial to paladins and protectors!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The discovery of this \"lynx\" created waves in noble circles when certain of their number realized they could have a feline around without succumbing to fur-based allergies. Now you see them everywhere.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silver-Gray Mouser Cat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Senchal Harbor-Mutt^M',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"These fastidious cats bring the blessing of Tu`whacca and hold a place of honor within their chosen homes. Further, they often start sleeping with any who near death, and thus we venerate them as guides to the Far Shores.\"—Tanandra, Scholar-Errant',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ask an Iliac Bay native what they`d miss most about their home and the answer might be the sight of tree-climbing spotted goats. Fortunately for these goat-lovers, the creatures now bleat their way from the bay to climb all manner of trees in new homes.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Rose-Eater' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Witch-Tamed Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Fur-rightful Fido' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Morthal Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'It`s the prestige of the mastiffs of Morthal that give the city`s resident breed of bear-dog license to be a bit more … silly. Whether watching over children or facing intruders, someone`s bound to get a licking.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'When merchants don`t arrive through the passes of the Jerall Mountains as expected, groups of searchers head out with these well-trained dogs to find them. More than a few winter caravans have these friendly dogs to thank for their lives.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Bretons have a strange practice of letting piebald cats loose in the secret passages of their manor homes. It stems from an ancient, noisy infestation of Sheogorath`s never-there beetles. It took years, but the clever felines eventually killed them all.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Neither-Nor' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'nickname' => 'Sir Bawk-Bawk' 
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Biscuit Bear-Dog',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Hunters often rely on the services of a loyal dog to protect them as they retrieve their kills. This breed not only ensures that their hunter remains well-guarded, but also provides quiet companionship.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'icon' => '/esoui/art/icons/pet_skingrad-guard-mastiff.dds',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These cats of Skyrim are used to harsh conditions with little respite. As a result, they`re quite hardy, known for their large size and thick, gorgeous fur. They`re prized by local villages for their mousing abilities and teeth-rattling purrs.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Silsailen Tortie-Calico Cat',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"First Creator, Final Destroyer. Void embrace the fallen and felled. Void devour the banished and judged. Void become me so that I may serve your will.\"—Death-Dancer Recitation',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A donkey might not be the most glamorous pack animal, but it`s certainly the hardiest and most sure-footed, toting heavy loads through desert, mountains, and tundra without complaint … though it will give you a dirty look, and might nip if you turn away!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The Nords of Hroldan started using their martial hammers for mining after a bloody skirmish involving miners and Reachfolk. Vowing to never again be caught flat-footed, they perfected this method over time and shared it with Nords throughout Skyrim.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Modern vosh balls are made of hard leather, but traditionalists insist on metal with a leather shell. Perfect for ore-mining practice throws.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'In seconds, this well-trained prairie dog can pilfer flora you need for your crafting. Be careful, this charming little rogue might steal your heart!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"The cold-flames speak to me. Will the flames speak to you, too, calling you to a master? Or perhaps you are a master—of bones? No matter. Go where your path leads, as I do. Perhaps we`ll meet next in Coldharbour?\"—Ymirra, Master of Bone and Scythe',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Study of the Great Source led to experimentation. And experimentation led to a convenience: near-instantaneous travel. Limitations exist for now. Still, I find it better than aching muscles after a long ride.\"—Excerpted from Firstborn Alenthe`s journal',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'World-Eater`s Fiery Recall',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Announce your exit—and your allegiance to—Alduin, the First Dragon. Perhaps those who gaze upon the fiery drama of your departure may seek to join you in worship of the World-Eater.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Wraith-of-Crows Woodchop',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'High rituals to the Shadow Queen require wood hewn by one of her Wraith-of-Crows.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Express your hilarious mockery of another with this over-the-top laugh emotion.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Ta-Dah!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ta-Dah!: an exaggerated emote from the theatrical House of Reveries on Summerset Isle.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Among the hard-bitten warriors of the Undaunted, no feat of dexterity is more admired than the Autumnal Ornamental Gourd Triple-Toss, also known as \"Jugglin` Pumpkins.\" Do you like hearty applause and sincere adulation? Try it!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Just a-carving away, yes, indeed.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Teeba Warm-Up',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Warm up for a rousing game of teeba-enoo, a popular Argonian pastime.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Show that you are prepared for a teeba kick-off with this ready stance.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Dead-Water Greeting',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Acknowledge others in the traditional battle-oriented manner of the Dead-Water tribe.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Nothing is more important to a self-respecting Khajiit than proper grooming! Clean those ears and whiskers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Ring in New Life with this festive bell-ringing emote!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'Pantomime Tug-of-War',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'There are various fairy-tale reasons for kissing a frog. Argonians prefer to taste them, to savor what they call \"amphibian brandy.\"',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Master the flow of energy in this kata from the Khajiiti order of Vrin-Thak.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Khajiiti merchants insist that this \"Dragon call\" can summon the beasts as surely as a duck-call summons waterfowl. While its effect on Dragons remains a matter of debate, everyone agrees that its clatter reliably attracts irritated friends and neighbors.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'The world can be an awful, terrible, no-good place filled with undead. Ward them all off with Arkay`s help. (Caution: Does not actually ward off undead.)',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Huh. Wait. No. Maybe this way? No? Who drew this so-called map?\"—every adventurer ever',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Toast your marshmallows and eat the ooey-gooey result. Tasty!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'These jerks are really asking for it! When you`re ready to settle an argument the old-fashioned way, express it with this aggressive emote.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'According to the Way of the Sword, the blade must become an extension of the body. Display a Redguard`s weapon-mastery with this stylish display!',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Re-enact the knighting ceremony held at Castle Navire, just as the Knight Commander does it. Your opinion of who is and is not a knight is somewhat less binding than hers.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Set the tempo for a proper celebration in the Green with this handpan crafted from bone. While the source of the bone may vary, all such instruments resonate similarly, allowing drummers to transition in and out of day-long performances smoothly.',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => '\"Ever played with magical fire? I mean, really played with it? Not just your standard yellow-orange flames. We`re talking colors. But which colors? So many choices. Even I can`t decide sometimes.\"—Thagbrugug, Budding Pyromancer',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'True-Sight Viewing',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'name' => 'World-Eater`s Fire Dance',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'Raise a banner in honor of your comrades-in-arms!\n\n|cFFFFFFAppearance is specific to your character`s alliance.|r',
esoCollectibleData.php:										'desc' => 'A traditional Vengeance Day dance, in celebration of retribution well-claimed in the previous year.',
